I'm a dance teacher at the royal Balletschool of Antwerp.
And I'm also a contemporary dancer, choreographer and photographer.

Be very welcome in my house, if you like creativity you're at the right place!

name: Design & luminous loft w/ view on canal
space: Located along the Canal de l'Ourcq this atypical Loft of 60sq. m. offers a wonderful view thanks to its numerous & large windows. Separated bedroom with a queen size bed (140cmx190), and several closets. Separated office that can be used as a guest room (2 futons 90cmx190cm). In our light flooded living room you'll find a large sofa (215cm), a confortable armchair, a nice coffee table, a large 4K TV (107cm) and a full collection of Blurays. You'll also have the possibility to enjoy a nice dinner (large table of 8 people) cooked in our fully equiped open kitchen (fridge & deep freezer, dishwasher, large kitchen worktop, microwave and fan oven, induction hobs, Nespresso coffee maker ...) The bathroom, spacious & fully renovated, is equiped with two wash-hand basins, a large italian shower & a washing machine. Fresh towels & bed sheets are at your disposal.

transit: Our flat is located less than 5 minutes away from Stalingrad (Lines 2,5,7) & Jaure (2,5, 7bis) subway stations. Velib stations closeby ( away : - Montmartre ( 3 subway stations away) - Louvre Museum - Beaubourg Museum - Opéra (Grands magasins, Opéra Garnier)  - Etienne Marcel/ Sentier/ Les Halles - Trendy districts of Belleville, Ménilmontant, & rue Saint Maur By foot or by bike : - Jardin de la Villette : 1100m - Buttes Chaumont square : 1200m - Canal Saint Martin district (Rues de Lancry/ Beaurepaire/ Marseille) with edgy shops, book stores, eco friendly grocery shops : 1800m, 5 minutes away by bike. Cab station located on Avenue de Flandre

name: Joli deux pièces
summary: Appartement bien situé, proche de toute commodité, épicerie, belleville montmartre, bar en tout genre. Situé sous les toits de paris. Accès à quelques minutes, le grand parc des buttes chaumont pour ce ressourcer, le canal de l'ourcq pour une petite dérive romantique et le parc de la villette.

host_about:
Bonjour à tous, 

 Ayant découvert ce site il y'a peu de temps grâce à un ami,  j'ai eu m'a première expérience sur Marseille. Cela m'a donné l'envie d’expérimenté à mon tour et me crée mon propre compte. Ce site me semble être le meilleur moyen de vraiment s'imprégné d'un lieux et de si sentir bien. Car on se sent vraiment chez soi.

C'est un appartement dans le 19eme arrondissement de paris, il fait 25 m2, 2 pièces, très lumineux, avec deux petits balcon sous les toits de paris.
Il est particulièrement bien situé, car le quartier et tranquille mais proche de toute commodité, on peut trouver 2 parc en moins de 10 minute à pied ( 2 minutes des Buttes Chaumont et 10 minutes du parc de la Villette canal de l'ourcq, vous pourrez y voir une multitudes d'événements l'été: festival, cinéma plein air... etc). Au pied de l'immeuble vous pourrez trouver une supérette, Pharmacie, restaurant, internet, café, esthéticien, ).

Il se trouve aussi très proche du quartier Belleville à pied 20 minutes.

C'est un appartement ou il fait bon vivre et qui est parfait pour un couple en vacance. 
L'appartement et équipé de vitrocéramique, d'un four, d'une machine à lavé étendoir, d'un poste de musique, d'un piano, d'un lit deux places.

J'espère que vous vous y plairez, car pour moi c'est un vrai cocon douillet.

A très bientôt et bon séjour sur Paris.

name: Cosy & Design, artists district
summary: Petit havre de paix à Saint-Gilles, la commune bruxelloise préférée des artistes...
space: Notre appartement est confortable, à la fois chaleureux, design et vintage. L'on s'y sent bien.  Aimez-vous les jardins et les expositions ? Cela tombe bien, nous avons un très joli jardin et nous exposons les artistes qui en font la demande. Dormir - Derrière la bibliothèque se cache une alcôve, bulle de douceur, avec son lit double  et dans la chambre, deux lits simples, en cabanes superposées, pour les petits ou pour les grands enfants.  Manger - Une cuisine bien équipée, une gazinière de grand-mère, une table ronde si conviviale. Se détendre - Un salon aux couleurs chaudes, aux meubles et aux objets design avec une superbe vue sur le jardin. Lire, écrire ou travailler - Une bibliothèque avec son très beau secrétaire restauré par nos soins. Prendre soin de soi - Une salle de bain vintage avec toilettes, lavabo et baignoire aux murs blancs et turquoises, miroir entouré de ses ampoules telle une loge de star. neighborhood_overview: Saint-Gilles est la commune de Bruxelles dont tout le monde parle et pour cause. De nombreux artistes y sont installés depuis des années et une culture bobo (marché bio, bars design, centre culturel, ...) a réussi son mariage avec la culture populaire et la mixité qui était déjà là.  Résultat, Saint-Gilles est un subtil mélange, en mieux, bien entendu, entre Marseille (pour son côté festif) et Berlin (pour son avant-gardisme). Pour se loger ou y habiter, Saint-Gilles est, certainement, the place to be. >>> en savoir plus : (URL HIDDEN)
notes: Exposition in situ. Nous exposons, sur nos murs, les oeuvres des artistes contemporains qui nous en font la demande. Pour le plaisir des yeux. Et si vous tombez amoureux de l'une d'entre elles, pas de souci, vous pouvez l'acquérir à prix d'amis.
transit: Tram, Bus ou Metro, rien de plus simple à Saint-Gilles pour se déplacer. A 10 min du Centre Ville, à 10 min de la Place Flagey à Ixelles, toutes les autres communes trouvent tout autant transports à leur pied.  >>> en savoir plus (URL HIDDEN) Garer sa voiture, le soir, à Bruxelles est une autre histoire, je ne vous la raconte pas,  quant au jour n'oubliez pas de vous munir de pièces, les parcmètres en raffolent. Comme les Vélib à Paris, à Bruxelles nous avons des Vilos!! >>> (URL HIDDEN)
interaction: Notre Best List, avec nos endroits de prédilections à Saint-Gilles vous attend. Restaurants, Marchés aux puces, Théâtres, Musées, Galeries d'art, Librairies, Bars, ... On vous dit tout.
house_rules: Nous n'avons pas de règles strictes. Nous vous demandons simplement de respecter notre maison et de prendre soin, comme votre propre maison. Nos meubles et nos objets ont été choisis avec amour et passion, nous nous occupons de notre équipement. Nous adorons cet endroit et nous sommes ravis de vous accueillir. - Pas de bruit à partir de 22h

Laurence and Eric from Bruxelles. 
Elle  : Artiste, femme, maman, amie, amoureuse, ...
Lui : Retail design manager, architecte commercial, adore faire la cuisine pour sa chérie et ses amis

name: The Best Location Studio Apartment
space: The apartment is fully furnished, including all bedding and towels. The apartment is always provided clean and tidy with the bed made with clean bedding and clean towels in the cupboard. There is wireless hi-speed internet with unlimited downloading. There's also an alarm clock radio. The bed is a double. There is a small fridge, double hotplate, large toaster oven, and regular toaster, plus dishes, pans, and utensils to cook whatever. There's a closet to hang clothes and to store bags etc.The studio is a comfortable and efficient space full of charm. In the daytime it is bright, thanks to the many windows, and cozy and intimate by night.  The studio is situated in the heart of the trendy Plateau neighborhood. The Plateau is the cultural heart and soul of Montreal. Physically, the studio is located at the epicenter of the city, so to get to all points on the Island is as efficient as can be. Notably Downtown Montreal is just an easygoing 20 minute walk away. Also it's only 20 minutes

Wisdom says "You can't make everybody happy all of the time", but I try anyway...

name: Unique Creative Apt. Piano. Bankside, Tate Modern
summary: Exceptional two bedroom flat full of art, books, antiques and music, including an electric piano.   SLEEPS 5 (One double, One double + single futon) Very light, quiet & central.  5 mins walk to Tate Modern, The Thames, Borough Market etc.  Oyster cards, £ change & Museum memberships provided!
space: - Exceptional two double bedroom flat  - Jammed full of art, books, antiques and music. There's nothing like it anywhere in London!  Spacious, lots of windows, very light.  - 5 mins walk from Tate Modern, The Thames, Borough Market etc. - Single futon under the stairs in the living room if required for 5th person. Visible as the low blue sofa in the photos. Outstanding and unusual home, both bang in the centre and surprisingly quiet. I've lived here for 8 years. Dual aspect windows, trains slide quietly and gracefully by outside. Upstairs attic bedroom, sleeping under the rafters.  Flat full of artworks, music, and books.  A small yard with acers and lillies.  Antique cast iron bath and separate shower cubicle. Large opening window in bathroom in you fancy having a bath gazing at the stars. Bath, shower, washing machine, usual kitchen things (no dishwasher). This is my home and it should be quite obvious that it's full of personal items and art. Maps of London and plenty of London book

neighborhood_overview: Best part of London, totally central, still just about quiet enough. The River Thames is a few minutes walk and straight across past Tate Modern to St Paul's Cathedral. Borough Market, the Golden Hinde, the Globe and the Shard are round the corner.  The best thing is to be close to the river and to cross it when you like.
notes: You can use my memberships to the Tate gallery, the British Museum and the Royal Academy of Art. These allow one or two people free entry to all the exhibitions, as well as use of the members room, which is particularly good at Tate modern, just around the corner.
transit: Right between London Bridge (Gatwick), Waterloo and Blackfriars (Luton).  Southwark, Borough, London Bridge and Waterloo tubes are all close. Plenty of busses. I provide a few free oystercards in the flat.
access: Bath, shower, washing machine, usual kitchen things (no dishwasher). This is my home and it should be quite obvious that it's full of personal items and art. Tate membership, Royal Academy membership, British Museum Membership cards provided.  Oystercards provided (to borrow). Spare change in £ and international currencies. Maps of London and plenty of London books and guides.  Wireless internet. Sheets, towels, soap provided. Basic foodstuffs provided.
interaction: I will always be available by phone.
house_rules: My flat is full of antiques and art, so a certain amount of respect and care is required. This is not the flat for parties or mucking around in. I happily accept families, couples, and workers, and tend not to accept students or groups of only young people. I also only accept airbnb members already with positive reviews. Sorry! Please note - I have two double beds, and one single futon which is normally in one of the bedrooms but which can be moved into the living room. If you are interested in a longer stay, please let me know.
host_about: I'm an editor of texts on child psychiatry and psychoanalysis. I play the piano and music is my main thing. I was born and live in London and this flat is my home, although I now mostly live in Marseille.
street: B Union Street, London, SE1 0LH, United Kingdom

name: Lovely private room in a serene Victorian house
summary: For an authentic and local London experience, stay in this strategically situated house in the heart of Peckham (Zone 2). Explore the neighbourhood by foot, you will be amazed by the charm and convenience this area has to offer. Before whisking off to the museums, sightseeing, shows or a shopping spree, enjoy a nice breakfast/brunch down at the nearby cafes. And, after a day of ‘city-trotting’, come back and replenish yourself with a meal in a local restaurant or unwind in a friendly local pub.
space: During your visit, you will be staying in a serene and cozy double bedroom on the first floor overlooking a gorgeous private garden. You will have full privacy in your own bedroom. Fresh linens and towels will be provided, there are hangers and plenty of space in the wardrobe for your use. You will also have a simple desk with desk lamp in the bedroom where you can use it for reading & writing, etc.  Items provided include: - Fresh towels and linens - Free WiFi - Hair dryer - Shower and hair shampoo - Travel adapters Additionally, we have also prepared a few London guidebooks, maps, and public transport leaflets, feel free to use them to discover some hidden gems in this interesting and happening city.

access: You are welcome to use all the communal areas within the property such as the kitchen, garden, shared bathroom & w.c, etc. We have a well equipped kitchen, you will find all the essentials for the preparation of your own meal, e.g. toaster, Nutribullet smoothie/juice blender, built-in oven, microwave oven, gas hob, French press & coffee maker, etc. We are happy to share the fridge with you, on top of that, you will get a designated drawer in the kitchen to keep your food as well.
interaction: We have written a guide book with local bars and cafes etc and will be happy to provide further information on request.
house_rules: We really like to keep the place clean and tidy, and we would appreciate it if our guests understand and respect this. Please clean up after yourself in the communal areas, particularly the bathroom and kitchen, leave the place clean and tidy, ready for the next person to enjoy using. - The house security measures need to be respected and used - Under 18's need to accompanied by a responsible adult - Quiet time after 11pm - Check out by 11am
host_about:
I am an artist who has lived in Peckham for the last 18 years, over the last few years I have also been teaching at Chelsea and Camberwell Colleges which are part of the University of the Arts London. 
I love food both cooking and eating and my tastes are eclectic, middle eastern, indian, thai and north african etc. 
I am very interested in film and photography and in the summertime I occasionally set up my garden cinema for an open air viewing. 
My music tastes are also eclectic and I particularly love world music from Africa my favourite radio station is Afriki Djigui Theatri who are based in Marseille France, check it out if you like this kind of music!

J'aime 
L'aventure, la découverte
Chercher, me perdre dans les rue d'une ville. 
Arriver en haut du sommet d'une montagne

L'honnêteté
Les saveurs des cuisines du monde entier (sauf le blanc d'oeuf baveux et la gélatine!)
La mer
La Bretagne, l'Irlande, l'Islande, la France, Paris, Marseille, Grenoble, Rennes, Toulouse, l'Italie, Venise, Rome, Bologna, l'Espagne, le Maroc, le Canada, Montréal, le Portugal, Berlin, Bruxelles, Istanbul et tant d'autres endroits d'où je garde de superbes souvenirs.

En voyage avec mon chum Jb (Jean-Baptiste), nous sommes le plus souvent des bagpackers, nous voyageons avec l'essentiel.

Dans la vie, nous travaillons tous les deux dans le milieu culturel.

neighborhood_overview: Paris 19, Belleville area, Buttes Chaumont : This is not a touristic area compared to Montmartre or le Marais but an authentic and lively Parisian district, with a popular background and long « melting pot » story. Round the corner are cafés, a baker, wine cellar, tobacco and newspaper store and the park Buttes Chaumont. 5 to 10 minutes away you reach the local supermarket « Franprix », the village « Jourdain » with all sorts of shops for food and the popular and multicultural Belleville with its asiatic restaurants… A little further you can walk along canal « la Villette », go to two movie houses and visit a trendy neighbourhood along the canal...
notes: Minimal stay : one week. A note about places to go to and things to do in the neighbourhood will be at your disposal. Winter season : the heating fee between 15th october untill 15th april is included in the renting price.
transit: Underground (metro) : station Pyrénées, line 11. Access to Pompidou Art Center and Châtelet (city center, junction with line RER B to Roissy airport) in 20mn. Bus n° 26 : access to Gare du Nord ( junction with RER B to Roissy airport, Eurostar, Thalys) in 20 mn. Velib’ station (self service bicycle round the corner).

host_about:
Couple éditeur chercheur. Intérêts: histoire contemporaine, environnement, art, cinéma, littérature. Nous passons la moitié de l'année en haute Provence, à mi-chemin de la montagne et de la mer, ce qui nous permet de randonner  dès que possible. Nous avons choisi cet appartement à cause de sa vue exceptionnelle, plus new yorkaise que parisienne, avec dans le lointain la rumeur de la ville et de la gare  mais surtout avec  le spectacle de (presque) tous les monuments de la capitale. La localisation de l'appartement nous a aussi séduits: tout à la fois en plein Paris, à dix minutes  à pied de la cinémathèque, des bords de Seine ou de la TGB, à vingt minutes  en métro du quartier latin  ou du Palais royal et à moins de dix minutes à pied du bois de Vincennes accessible à pied ou en vélo par la coulée verte, la high line parisienne.
Nous avons trois enfants, l'un vit en Inde, l'autre à Marseille, le dernier à Paris. Paris est un bon lieu pour se retrouver quand ils le peuvent. Nous y passons l'hiver mais l'été et l'automne nous sommes dans le midi ou à l'étranger, d'où l'idée de louer notre appartement.

host_about: Les joies simples de la vie avec nos deux marmots (Sacha, 4,5 ans et Alfred, 2,5 ans), les amis, les bonnes choses, les rencontres et les voyages, voilà ce qui pourrait nous caractériser laconiquement. Parisiens d'adoption (Marie, 34 ans - mon épouse - est originaire de Marseille et moi-même (35 ans) des Flandres), nous avions a priori peu de repères communs ; Paris fut peut-être le premier et avons décidé d'en faire notre nid ; tous 2 amoureux de campagne et de retranchement, rien ne laissait présager que nous y poserions nos valises et que Paris deviendrait notre ville et celle de nos enfants - et pourtant - depuis près de 10 ans nous y sommes des plus heureux. Cette ville est fascinante ; son histoire, son atmosphère, ses petites adresses de quartier, son pluralisme, ses charmantes parisiennes..., la rende paisible et magique à la fois. Après avoir investi notre nouvel appartement fraichement rénové fin 2014, nous nous sommes lancés sur Air BNB pour vivre cette aventure basée sur des valeurs qui nous plaisent, la confiance et le partage. Nous pensons aussi qu'il s'agit d'un formidable moyen de recréer du lien. Venez vite vous évader loin de chez vous, nous serons ravis de vous y accueillir et de tout mettre en œuvre pour que votre séjour soit un merveilleux souvenir. Welcome in Paris ! A bientôt, Edouard, Marie, Sacha et Alfred.

neighborhood_overview: The 11th district of Paris is situated on the right bank of the Seine between the Nation places, the Republic and Bastille. Discreet district, less touristy than others, the 11th played an exceptional role in the history of Paris and France. He was at the heart of revolutionary Paris and major workers' revolts of the nineteenth century. Formerly working-class neighborhood welcoming a dense network of small businesses, the 11th district is now a "cool" district especially towards the Place de la Bastille, rue Oberkampf or the rue de Lappe, due to the installation of bars and nightclubs.

host_about:
Bonjour, je m’appelle Romain ! 

Ayant été hôte sur Airbnb à Marseille avec succès, j’ai appris à connaître les attentes des hôtes et des voyageurs. Je suis également passionné par le secteur tourisme et possède des expériences marquantes en locations touristiques. 

De nature entrepreneur, j’ai créé Renty. Renty c’est le premier label à travers Airbnb qui assure les voyageurs d’une qualité élevée et de services hauts de gamme. Cela vous permet, en tant que voyageur, de bénéficier d’un panier accueil, de produits d’hygiène, d’informations touristiques, d’une assistance téléphonique 7j/7 de 9h à 22h. 

Renty permet également de faciliter la vie aux hôtes en gérant à leur place leur activité sur Airbnb. Il n’est en effet pas toujours simple pour eux de concilier la gestion de cette activité et leur vie professionnelle, leur vie personnelle, leurs loisirs, … 

Renty, c’est également des services ponctuels et de dépannage pour les hôtes occasionnels ou ne louant qu’une partie de leur logement. 

N’hésitez pas à me contacter pour plus d’informations sur mon activité, je serai heureux d’y répondre !

Bus station within 5 mns walk
access: This apartement is an authentic parisian apartment, where we live when we are in Paris (it's not a tourist dedicated apt). Some of the cabinets are consequently not available. But we managed so that you have space enough in every room and feel just like at home.
interaction: We want you to FEEL AT HOME and LIKE A REAL PARISIAN :) We are personnaly and totally invested in our guests having a wonderful experience :  ❤ We provide you with : - A 20 PAGES NEIGHBORHOOD GUIDE  of all our best places : where to buy your baguette, your cheese & wine,  fruits & veggetables market, where to have a drink or diner, but also sightseing and of course shopping !  - A 4 PAGES ACCESS GUIDE from airport and railway stations to the apartment, including prices and time. - A LOGISTICAL HOME GUIDE for all electrical appliances, wifi, emergency... ❤ We welcome you personally, answer all your questions, and help you organizing your stay if you wish. ❤ Before your arrival, during and after your stay, we will always be available for you by mail or via phone. ==> In order to optimize your welcome, please inform us as soon as possible about your arrival et departure details (train/flight number). Thanks !
house_rules: Some information to make you and us comfortable with your stay in #YourEiffelHome :) CHILDREN (< 18 years) :  No children for security reasons : no specific protection, especially, but not exhaustively on the high floor balcony. CONFIDENCE & VERIFICATION : Because this apt is our personal typical parisian apt, we prefer to host serious and reliable guests and thus ask  Airbnb verified profile for the person who ask for the booking + name of the accompanying person. HOUSE RULES : - No walk on the building garden lawn - No noise after 10 PM - No extra guests or visitors :  only the persons whose name has been registered in the booking may enter the apt. In case you want to book a photographer, just let us know his name. - No item left on the floor landing (shoes, umbrella etc ...) - Strictly non smoking, including balcony (as we are allergic)  - White and fragile wooden floor, please use the slippers at your disposal or walk without shoes ... USE OF THE APARTMENT :  - No business, no sho
host_about:
Airbnb guests since sept 2015 - Airbnb hosts since sept 2016
My husband and myself are happy young retirees... Philippe was working in finance while I was working in marketing/communication.
We love music (especially jazz, but not only), cinema, pop art, art deco (modern style), good food (I have a good cook reputation …), welcoming family and friends at home, and travelling. 
We are very concerned about the welfare of the earth and are living an eco friendly lifestyle (homemade bio cleaning products, linens washed with Marseille soap only etc ...).
We have travelled all over the world when we were working. Our favorite destinations are the US, Japon and Asia . Of course we intend to carry on now we have more time, it's so exciting to discover other cultures. 
We recently fully refurbished our apartment and have decided to welcome you and share with you the chance we have to enjoy this beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower. 
Our  goal is that you feel perfectly well in Your Eiffel Home and that you keep a wonderful memory of your stay in Paris !

interaction: Je parle français, anglais, portugais et me débrouille en espagnol; mais ne suis pas souvent présente pour accueillir les visiteurs car j'habite la plupart du temps en Provence. (avons également un appartement à Marseille que nous louons). C'est mon amie Danièle qui s'en charge ou ma belle-soeur Maïa qui habite tout à côté (professeur de français pour étrangers qui en plus des langues ci-dessus parle italien). Moi-même et mon mari voyageons beaucoup et louons des appartements par Airbnb. Sommes devenus amis avec 2 locataires qui avaient loués par Lodgis : des canadiens et des suédois qui reviennent régulièrement.
house_rules: Nous ne préférons pas que l'on fume dans l'appartement. Sauf éventuellement à le fenêtre du salon. Merci d'avance.
host_about:
Mariée, à la retraite, je partage ma vie entre Paris et la Provence. Ancienne dirigeante d'une agence de publicité parisienne, je m'occupe maintenant de développement de colorants végétaux en Provence : indigo, garance, réséda.... J'adore aussi naviguer à la voile et faire des voyages.
Arts, architecture, lecture, sont, en plus de la botanique mes centres d'intérêt.
J'aime recevoir des étrangers dans mon appartement, qui deviennent parfois des amis. Quand je voyage c'est souvent avec Airbnb.

neighborhood_overview: It is a neighborhood that I like very much, it is quiet and there are a lot of families and schools nearby, there are plenty of small squares and pedestrian streets. The 20th district is really nice to live with plenty of shops, nice restaurants and bookstores, small pedestrian streets, etc. There are also several theaters and a cinema a few minutes walk away. My favorite places: rue de Chine there is my favorite bar "les chaises", opposite there is a super italian "atelier fratelli", and a little before in the street there is a great restaurant-wine cellar "Le tablier rouge". There is also a lovely little restorant very close by: "chez elle" 3 rue des tourelles, which also makes brunch on weekends. There are several supermarkets all around the studio, bakeries, and a market around the metro telegraph 3 days a week. On Sunday morning there is a big market at Place des Fêtes, a 10 min walk. For walking, there is the park of Belleville not far, as well as the famous cemetery of Père Lach
transit: The apartment is very well served by public transport: Metro : - Just next to line 11, short and fast line which will take you in 10 min to Belleville, in 15 min to République and in 20 minutes to châtelet. This is the best metro line in Paris! - The line 3bis is right next to the stop saint fargeau (it is clearly less useful ...) Bus: - There are also bus lines (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN) and 96 which are closeby - it is very nice to take the bus, especially on weekends, to enjoy the city and admire the beautiful streets of Paris. It's sometimes a bit longer than the subway, but so much nicer! - And for night owls, the night bus N12 will take you back at any time of the night, next to the apartment ;) Tramway: - the T3b line passes very close too, it is a very pleasant way to go to the Philarmonie, the Parc de La Villette, the Cité des Sciences, but also the Parc de Vincennes But I advise you to walk to the maximum: Paris is a small capital and all the neighborhoods are beautiful and it is
access: The apartment is small but fully equipped - there is everything to cook (Fridge, oven, mixer, induction plates, plates, kettle guaranteed without BPA - endocrinal disruptors), - a small but practical bathroom with plenty of hot water (hair dryer, reader, curling iron, washing machine, etc.) - stay connected with the high speed optical fiber internet And of course a nice space to relax on the couch or the pouffes, benefiting from the sun that comes in abundantly in this south-east facing apartment: you will be woken up by the rays of the sun in the morning :) In the neighborhood there are plenty of grocery shops, a bakery around the corner, a post office, but also small nice restaurants to hang out or have diner, a drink, etc. I will give you my favorite addresses!
interaction: Je peux vous expliquer où tout se situe dans l'appartement et dans le quartier, et je vous partagerai mes bonnes adresses :)  L'hospitalité est très importante pour moi et je m'assurerai que vous passiez un bon séjour à Paris.  Je reste joignable durant votre séjour, sauf si je suis moi-même hors de France avec un accès limité au téléphone/ internet.
house_rules: Faites comme chez vous : donc respectez mon chez-moi comme vous respectez le vôtre !

Jeune femme active, je travaille dans la promotion de l'entrepreneuriat social et des méthodes de travail collaboratives. 
J'aime voyager, les belles choses et le bon vin ! 

Je viens de Marseille, et l'hospitalité est l'une des valeurs centrales de la culture provençale. J'ai fait pas mal de couch surfing et de voyage chez l'habitant, j'aime recevoir et échanger !

neighborhood_overview: NEIGHBORHOOD LIFE  -------------------------- A quiet Paris neighborhood bordering a tree-lined, Napoleon-era canal draws a young, creative crowd that appreciates its picturesque atmosphere, hip boutiques, lively wine bars, and well-priced eateries. As the area gains popularity, new boutiques, cafés, and restaurants keep cropping up on both sides of the canal. The main shopping streets include rue Beaurepaire, rue Yves Toudic, rue de Marseille, and rue de Lancry. Stroll along the Quai de Valmy for its wonderful cafés and bistros, then cross the arching bridge over to the Quai de Jemmapes, where you'll find the old Hotel de Nord, the historic Hôpital Saint-Louis, superb dining spots, and myriad hidden gems. We suggest spending a few days exploring the neighborhood's best haunts, from shiny new shops and chic just-opened cafés to old favorites. You'll be strolling the rues like a local in no time. In spring and summer, you will enjoy boat cruises on the Canal, picnic and children playgro
notes: The bells of the church can be heard from the apartment. It contributes to the charm, but might bother some.

I like creating, singing, dancing and good music and practice yoga. 

Come to have a great time in Paris, visiting this mythic town. The place here is peaceful and bright. I can give you some ideas of visiting and will answer to your question about Paris and the great place to go. 
Welcome...

I like this french expression "vivons heureux, vivons cachés" translation "To live happy, let's live secretly"

name: Central cosy room in the heart of Paris
summary: We have ready for you a very cosy bedroom in our apartment in the most central place in Paris, just in front of the Forum des Halles, two minutes away from Pompidou center, Notre-Dame and Louvre, yet in a very calm location.
space: We have ready for you a small cosy bedroom in our apartment in the center of Paris, steps away from the Forum des Halles. The neighborhood is really in the center of Paris and most landmarks are walking distance away (see below). The living room, kitchen and bathroom are shared. The bedroom is small, but has lots of light and is very quiet as it opens on the interior court. The bed is a real bed for two with a real mattress, not a sofa bed. Please note that the apartment is at the 5th floor, and unfortunately the lift only goes 1 floor up, making it 4 floors to climb, but it's good exercice ;-).

Please note that the apartment is at the 5th floor, and unfortunately the lift only goes 1 floor up, making it 4 floors to climb, but it's good exercice ;-). Guests have their own private bedroom with a bed for 2. Guests will be welcome to use the living room, kitchen and bathroom that are shared with us. Our bedroom is private.
neighborhood_overview: Our apartment in really located in the center of Paris and all major central landmarks are accessible by foot. Our apartment is located between the Forum des Halles (1mn) and Centre Pompidou (modern art museum) (2mn), the neighborhood is lively and you will find restaurants, and shops just out the door, and markets on weekends. The rue Montorgueil (5mn) with its famous market is steps away and open on weekends. In 8mn, you will find the Hôtel de Ville, the BHV shopping center and Tour Saint Jacques. Going in the direction of the river and Place du Chatelêt (5mn), you can cross La Seine to go on the île de la Cité toward Notre-Dame de Paris (10mn) and the Quartier Latin (15mn). Le Louvre is 11mn away. All distances and times are walking distance according to (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) Maps.
notes: Please that sometimes if we are away for a long period, we will rent the while apartment. It will appear on a separate listing.
transit: Chatelêt-les-Halles is THE central metro hub in Paris, with service for multiple metro lines (1,4,7,11,14) RER A, B et D.  By metro, you can reach Gare du Nord (for trains from/to UK,Belgium,Netherlands) in 5mn with RER B, Gare de Lyon (for trains from/to Zurich, Marseilles, Grenoble, Geneva) in 5mn with RER A, and Gare Montparnasse with metro 4 (for Nantes, Brittany, south-west of France). By plane, airport Charles de Gaulle (CDG) is directly accessible with RER B (45mn), and Orly airport is accessible with RER B (to Denfert-Rochereau, 6mn) then OrlyBus (30mn). For biking lovers, there is a public bike rental just in outside the building front door.
access: Guests have their own private bedroom with a bed for 2. Guests will be welcome to use the living room, kitchen and bathroom that are shared with us. Our bedroom is private.
interaction: French, English and Chinese spoken.  We will have a map and a few guides ready for you (Routard and Michelin) and would be happy to show you our favorite restaurants around. We will be living in the apartment.
house_rules: Merci de ne pas fumer dans l'appartement.  Malheureusement, nous n'avons pas l'espace d'accueillir nos amis les animaux.
host_about: We love to travel and to discover new places all around the world, and that's why we love to share our city to others from everywhere.

You will cross a beautiful courtyard equipped with bike storage before accessing it. The studio overlooks the courtyard, so it is very quiet. You will enjoy t
neighborhood_overview: The accommodation is located at the crossroads of 3 of the most famous districts of Paris. These districts are very old and you will be charmed by their authenticity. The accommodation is mainly in the Saint Germain des Prés district. It is well known for hosting some of the oldest buildings in Paris dating back to the middle-age. It is also a very rich district that hosts many luxury boutiques and designers, and it is not uncommon to meet celebrities. As an extension of Saint-Germain des Prés is the Odeon district. Very charming also, do not forget to take a coffee at the famous Café de Flore. Little further is the Latin Quarter. Very well known for its magnificent medieval buildings and for its universities known throughout the world (La Sorbonne in particular). Do not miss the delightful Jardin du Luxembourg (relax in the sun on one of the many free chairs), the Panthéon (in the pathway of Victor Hugo ...), the Sorbonne, Place Saint- Michel. The studio is also very close to the Ile
transit: There are a lot of transports: RER B and C (Saint-Michel), metro line 4 (Saint-Germain des Prés), metro line 10 (Mabillon / Odéon) and metro line 12 a little further (rue du Bac). Many bus lines. Velib and Autolib stations. Many monuments are within walking distance.
access: Checkin from 3 pm to 11.30 pm. I will be present to welcome you.    Check-out is before noon (midday / 12 pm).
interaction: I will contact you during your stay to be sure everything is alright and that you enjoy your stay.    In case of problem or if you have a question feel free to contact me throughout your stay by phone, email or via Airbnb. I'm happy to bring you my help.   Thank you not to call between 10 pm and 8 am, except for emergencies. Rather send me a message, I will answer quickly.
host_about:
Bonjour, je m’appelle Romain ! 

Ayant été hôte sur Airbnb à Marseille avec succès, j’ai appris à connaître les attentes des hôtes et des voyageurs. Je suis également passionné par le secteur tourisme et possède des expériences marquantes en locations touristiques. 

De nature entrepreneur, j’ai créé Renty. Renty c’est le premier label à travers Airbnb qui assure les voyageurs d’une qualité élevée et de services hauts de gamme. Cela vous permet, en tant que voyageur, de bénéficier d’un panier accueil, de produits d’hygiène, d’informations touristiques, d’une assistance téléphonique 7j/7 de 9h à 22h. 

Renty permet également de faciliter la vie aux hôtes en gérant à leur place leur activité sur Airbnb. Il n’est en effet pas toujours simple pour eux de concilier la gestion de cette activité et leur vie professionnelle, leur vie personnelle, leurs loisirs, … 

Renty, c’est également des services ponctuels et de dépannage pour les hôtes occasionnels ou ne louant qu’une partie de leur logement. 

N’hésitez pas à me contacter pour plus d’informations sur mon activité, je serai heureux d’y répondre !

neighborhood_overview: The Historic 7th Ward, also known as New Marigny or lower Treme, is a realistic and funky New Orleans neighborhood, a close walk to the hip Marigny neighborhood, adjacent to the French Quarter.  Renovations are happening all around this historically working class, Black, Creole, and Italian community because of its proximity to the Marigny, French Quarter, and Bywater, its historic architecture, and its affordability. The Seventh Ward is rich in cultural history, home of Jelly Roll Morton, Sidney Bechet, civil rights activists, Mardi Gras Indians, Brass Bands, and Second Line parades.   I have been a resident for 15 years and feel at home here.  As in any neighborhood in New Orleans use common sense where safety is concerned.  I do recommend that after dark that you take an Uber or a cab to get around, as I would recommend in any area of New Orleans.
notes: This property is a private residence.  The homeowner is not responsible or liable for any accidents, injuries or illness that might occur while on the premises or its facilities.  - Queen size bed  - Bath has step-in Japanese shower  -Studio is equipped with a mini-fridge, microwave, radio, coffee maker, and electric kettle (no stove).
transit: This studio is 2 blocks from St. Claude Avenue where city buses can take you downriver to Bywater or upriver to the Garden District, Uptown and beyond.  It is very convenient to walk, bike or take taxis from here.  There are multiple bike rental companies in New Orleans and plenty of space to park and lock them in the secure, gated backyard.   If you have a car while visiting, there is off street parking for 1 vehicle.  Parking is first come, first served on the street and unless there is a special event, typically easy to find parking.

neighborhood_overview: The Sainte Marthe area, popular area long time ago became over the years a trendy place in the capital. In the heart of the picturesque quarter is a charming and unusual place, which has a pleasant atmosphere of tranquility. Once home to many foremen and construction workers, it is a corner to village air, cosmopolitan and multicultural today, whose activities are more shopping and craft. Sainte-Marthe is a neighborhood inhabitants, without many people passing and animating rather evening, a place to popular fiber which remained authentic and full of character, in Paris yet becoming increasingly sanitized. This is where lies the small, leafy place Sainte-Marthe, almost invisible in the middle of a network of narrow streets. Among them stands out the peculiar rue Sainte-Marthe, who with his machine to windows and its small side méridionnal recalls the streets of Naples or Marseille. Steeped in art and culture, not only photogenic, this place is an authentic life with terraces of cafes,

neighborhood_overview: Historic Capitol Hill is full of beautiful old homes, close to parks and a short walk to the US Capitol, the Library of Congress, the Supreme Court, the Folger Shakespeare Museum, and the National Mall. It is also close to the National Gallery of Art, the Botanical Garden, and the Air and Space Museum. Eastern Market is a 15 minute walk with amazing coffee, brunch, and dinner spots. The weekend it's home to a flea market and filled with local farm vendors who sell organic fruits, vegetables, and homemade cheeses. The market has an amazing selection of fish, seafood, meats, and homemade pastas. Barracks Row just beyond Eastern Market has numerous restaurants of every cuisine. H street Northeast is also just a short walk away, with many new restaurants, great Ethiopian food, coffee shops, and yoga studios. Further up Union Market has an amazing selection of food and pastry vendors, including a locally sourced oyster bar and Korean tacos.
notes: Some closet space will be provided.
transit: Short walk to Eastern Market, H Street NE, and Union Station.  Bike lanes are plentiful and the neighborhood is extremely safe and walkable. Bike share dock is one block away and I am happy to let you borrow my access key.  You can hop on the red line at Union Station (either a 15 min walk or a 5 min bus ride) and on the orange/blue line at Eastern Market. Bus transit is widely accessible and picks you up a block away. My apartment is about a 15/20 minute taxi ride from Reagan Int'l (DCA) airport and easily accessed by subway.
access: You will have access to high speed internet, Chromecast, a washer and dryer in the unit, and central A/C and heat. You are also welcome to hang out in the backyard on my lounge chair.
interaction: I am available at your convenience via text, call, or email. I am happy to suggest restaurants and activities in the neighborhood or anywhere in DC.  I also have a welcome book that I will leave with you.
house_rules: No pets of any kind, nor parties or loud music, please. Upon leaving, all doors and windows must be shut/locked. Oven and stove-top usage in kitchen is welcomed, but please do not leave the apartment while anything is cooking. Trash must be dumped behind the apartment complex.

name: Spacious apartment in Paris
summary: Hi ! If you are coming to Paris, I would be happy to be your host ! Our big one room apartment is very confortable and ideally located in a central and exciting part of Paris, 1 minute away from 'place de la République', close to the canal St Martin.
space: The apartment is in the center of the parisian right bank (of the Seine river) which allows you to access the city by foot and take the time to wander through parisian marvels. It is also very central for public transportation (Metro station 'République' has 5 different metros) and for taxis as the taxi stand is 100 yards away from the apartment. The apartment is 820 square feet so there is a lot of space to rest after a long city's walk.  A cute entry way will lead you to the living room there is a fold out couch which can be practical if there are more than 2 of you coming over. There is a nice sized room with lots of shelves to put clothes away. The kitchen is big enough that we eat most of our meals there. And there is a nice sized bathroom with big shower and bathtub, which are just perfect to unwind after visiting Paris. We have many plants and a lot more books !!!

neighborhood_overview: The place de la République was redone in june 2013 which adds to the liveliness of the neighborhood : there an outside game café with a ton of games for children, a café with a water mirror great for toddlers, and of course a lot of animation such as concerts or cultural events. And all of this is just a minute away from the apartment. You will also be close to Belleville if you go towards the north or the Beaubourg section (modern art museum) if you are southbound. The famous marais quarter is only 15 minutes away by foot. And of course, there is the Canal St Martin : you can simply walk along it, sit down and have a drink or just take a look around. And if you like water, you can walk down Richard Lenoir avenue until you reach the 'Arsenal' (a small marina next to Bastille) which is a very pleasant place to picnic or have a drink. And for the serial-shoppers : Maje, Les Petites et Claudie Pierlot have their outlets just 5 minutes away from the apartment on rue de Marseille. Lots of c
transit: The metro subway station is République : lines 3, 5, 8, 9 and 11 go through this station. Buses : 20, 56, 65 et 75. Bike station 'vélibs' are just 2 minutes away. Trains : all train stations are linked through the metro to République except for Montparnasse Station. Airports (Charles de Gaulle or Orly) : RER B until you reach Gare du nord, then 3 stations with métro line 5 will lead you to République.
access: If you are planing on staying a while, we will clear out some space for your clothes and you can use our facilities (washing machine). Don't worry, we can lend towels (but we do not have wash clothes). Regarding the kitchen, if you don't feel like taking advantage of one of the cool restaurants in our neighborhood, you can also cook in the apartment : we have an oven, a stove and a microwave.
interaction: Feel free to ask any questions you may have !  I was born in Paris and I love my city, so it would be quite a pleasure to share what I know. I have used this airbnb site for housing in foreign countries and I know how much good tips are appreciated ! I also love good food and will more than glad to share the addresses of a few of my favorite restaurants with you. I also check my emails regularly so I should be able to answer any questions you have quickly !!
house_rules: Sorry but animals and smoking are forbidden in our home !
host_about: I'm Sarah : a 38 yo French teacher who likes to travel (Thailand, Sweden, Norway, Cuba, Slovenia, Croatia, Israel, Egypt, Italy, Spain, Turkey, US, Canada, Iceland, Singapore, Indonesia and many to come...).

name: Charming apartment - Tour Eiffel
summary: This bright apartment is located on the 5th floor with elevator of a Haussmann building with 2 security codes. It has a balcony over the entire length of the apartment. It has been completely renovated but retains the charm of the old (fireplaces, parquet flooring and moldings). Located along the Seine, 2 steps from the Eiffel Tower and near the new shopping center Beaugrenelle. The subway "Bir Hakeim Tour Eiffel" is 50m and you can reach in no time all the important places in Paris.
space: The renovated apartment consists of a large entrance, a living room with balcony and 1 coach which is a single bed, an open kitchen on the living room, a bedroom with balcony and double bed 160cm wide, a bathroom with shower and a separate toilet. The access to the building is secured by 2 digital codes. We provide free use of towels and toiletries as well as a linen kit (soap, shampoo, hairdryer). You also have high speed internet/Wifi access by optical fiber cable and international news channels.

neighborhood_overview: The area has all the useful shops nearby (supermarket, organic store, pharmacy, bakery Poilane, Delicatessen ). A market holds twice a week under the metro line (duplex Motte Piquet Grenelle). At 5 minutes walk, the Lourmel street is renowned for its food stores  (cheese, meat, vegetables). The new Beaugrenelle shopping center (110 shops, restaurants, cinemas) at 10 minutes walk from the apartment  is the ideal place for shopping. Crossing the street you can walk or ride a bicycle along the Seine river sides (the cars have no access) and access the main monuments (the Eiffel Tower, les Invalides, le Grand Palais , the Champs Elysées, Saint Germain des prés, Notre Dame, …)
notes: Maps and guides are available on loan and I would love before your stay to advise you according to your visits wishes.
transit: 50 meters from the apartment is the access to the metro station "Bir Hakeim Eiffel-Tower" (line 6). This outdoor subway line section will carry you to the Champs Elysées and will  provides one of the best view of the Eiffel Tower from the bridge over the Seine river. At 70 meters, the access to the RER station "Champ de Mars" (line C) allows you to go directly to the château offre Versailles or through Paris along the Seine. Several bike rental stations (Vélib) are available near the building.

name: Charming & handy apartment - Parisian lifestyle
summary: Located right in the middle of young and “real” Paris, my apartment is super convenient & comfortable. It’s perfectly sized for a week-end or longer, whether you’re a couple or traveling solo, for touristic or business purpose. Situé au centre du Paris jeune et véritable, mon appartement est très pratique et confortable. Sa taille le rend parfait pour un week-end ou plus longtemps, que vous soyez seul(e) ou à deux, pour du tourisme ou en voyage d’affaires.
space: I have high standards for the environment I live in so I made my apartment as nice & comfortable as possible. It is bright and peaceful (due to large windows and the fact it opens on a courtyard, not the street contrary to many Parisian apartments). My friends love it, I hope you will as well. - Bed: Due to the sacred status of my sleep, the bed quality is really good. Also, its size suits actually tall people.  - Kitchen: equipped with hot plates, a steam cooker, a kettle, all the necessary kitchen utensils and dishes for up to 4 people (including wine glasses and cheese grater). The kitchen table is currently for 2 people but can be extended for 4.  - Couch: my convertible sofa is large enough to be used as a bed for a kid in case you need it (but not for an adult).

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located at the crossing of some of the best districts where Parisians actually spend their time: Canal Saint-Martin to chill in trendy places and stroll along the canal, Buttes Chaumont for sport or drinks and picnics in the park, Gare du Nord - Gare de l’Est for easy access and multicultural experiences, and La Villette for cultural activities and walking in wide spaces. For sporty people: the location is perfect if you like a little (or long !) jog, cycling along the two canals (+ practical in terms of cycling paths towards most directions), swimming (5 min walk to the Chateau Landon swimming pool), and basketball (10 min walk to a court).
notes: Please note I put this apartment on Airbnb not to make any profit but to help pay my heavy rent while I’m away. This means I’d like to welcome people who will take care of an environment I’ve put a lot of attention and efforts (& money!) into making nice and comfortable. Also, following an article I read about Airbnb discrimination, I’d like to state out loud that I’m happy to share my beloved place to everyone who’d like to enjoy it like I do. I live in a calm building with all sorts of people including families and older people, and I’d like to keep good relations with my neighbours. Please respect this calm environment (no parties, no super loud music).
transit: In terms of arriving from other parts of the world/other parts of France: 10 min walk from Gare du Nord (Eurostar + transport to CDG & Orly Airports) & Gare de l’Est (Thalys trains). In terms of living the Parisian life: My apartment is nearby or less than 20 min away from places where most of the young Parisians go out (surrounding districts + République/Bastille/Pigalle). In terms of discovering the beauty Paris has to offer: My apartment is located less than 30 min away from many touristic locations as well. For example (with public transports):  Louvre museum 19 min, Pigalle 12 min, Trocadéro 26 min, Champs Elysées 23 min, Centre Pompidou 18 min, Quartier Latin 25 min, Musée d’Orsay 26 min.  In terms of reaching "business districts”: 15 min from the Richelieu-Drouot area, 20 min from the Ternes area, 27 min from La Défense. Metro lines 2, 4, 5, 7, 7bis. RER : B, D, E. Many different buses. Vélib’ (Paris 24/7 bike sharing system):  3 different stations 3 min away.
access: You'll have access to my whole apartment. If you come with your own bike, you'll have access to the building's bike storage room.
interaction: I’ll be happy to give you all the info you need to enjoy a nice stay before you arrive, just ask :) During your stay, I’ll be available by text message ((SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN)) & mail. Several friends live nearby (although it shouldn’t be necessary).
house_rules: - No noise after 10pm - Pas de bruit après 10h du soir
host_about:
[Français plus bas]

Hello, 
I'm a young Parisian coming from South of France (Marseilles). I like music, spending time with people, and all things beautiful and harmonious. 
My favourite musicians are David Bowie and Chet Baker, my favourite movie is Mon Oncle by Jacques Tati.
I work as a brand strategist specialized in sound design, and I also dedicate a bit of time to volunteer in various associations. 
I’ve been living in Paris for almost 10 years, and in many different areas, so I’d be happy to help you with good advices of things to do and places to go in my neighbourhood or further in the city !

Bonjour, 
Je suis une Marseillaise à Paris. J’aime la musique, passer du temps avec d’autres personnes, et tout ce qui est emprunt de beauté et d’harmonie.
Mes musiciens préférés sont David Bowie et Chet Baker, mon film préféré est Mon Oncle de Jacques Tati. 
Je travaille dans la stratégie de marque du point de vue sonore, et je passe aussi un certain temps à être bénévole dans différentes associations. 
J’ai déjà passé presque 10 ans à Paris, ce qui me rend très familière de bon nombre d’endroits où j’ai vécu ou travaillé. Je serai donc très heureuse de partager avec vous mes conseils, pour explorer mon quartier comme l’ensemble de la ville !

name: Charming apartment next to Retiro
summary: Lovely private 3 bedroom apartment in the center of Madrid next to the park of Retiro. Very well connected. Situated in lively neighbourhood. The apartment is a real welcoming heaven to relax and feel at home while living a Spanish experience.
space: Luxury private three bedroom apartment in the center of Madrid next to the park of Retiro, a stunning blend of formal gardens, soaring monuments and wild, wooded areas. The charming apartment is in a privileged and tranquil location well within reach of the city centre, on the 4st floor (with lift) of an elegant building from the 19th century. The apartment is an elegant and refined interior decoration with pleasant mix of classical and modern styles, warm and cozy. You will find 3 bedrooms (2 bedrooms with double bed, 1 bedroom with 2 single beds), two bathrooms and a large living-dining room with beautiful and long basque style wooden table, a confurtable sunny, bright and spacious living room with two sofas and TV corner. The kitchen is fully furnished. All rooms are air conditioned and have high speed internet and wifi. An apartment where you can relax comfortably after a busy day in Madrid.

name: Your Nest Over Paris Roofs & Sight
summary: Bright cocoon 15 min walking to Gare Montparnasse, Champs de Mars (Tour Eiffel), and Invalides. Absolute calm at 8th floor (no elevator), near charming neighborhoods (7e, 6e). 27m² (3 rooms) to enjoy Paris!
space: Welcome traveler!! Welcome in your little nest in Paris!! :-) The flat is highly bright (mainly in the living room), and really calm. I bet you may not feel more peaceful in Paris. And it is really easy to cool down here, from turbulent Parisian life below. Both living room and bedrooms also have nice sights, as the flat is 1 floor higher than all other buildings.  Globally, the flat is brand new, simple, central, and very functional! During your stay, you'll have access to your bedroom, the living room + kitchen and the bathroom with WC. The 2 bedrooms (yours and the roommate's) are separated by the living room. Even if my roommate is really awsome!! ;-) Little towels and bed sheets are provided. The bedroom to rent can host 2 persons.

Welcome in your little nest in Paris!! :-) The flat is highly bright (mainly in the living room), and really calm. I bet you may not feel more peaceful in Paris. And it is really easy to cool down here, from turbulent Parisian life below. Both living room and bedrooms also have nice sights, as the flat is 1 floor higher than all other buildings.  Globally, the flat is brand new, simple, central, and very functional! During your stay, you'll have access to your bedroom, the living room + kitchen and the bathroom with WC. The 2 bedrooms (yours and the roommate's) are separated by the living room. Even if my roommate is really awsome!! ;-) Little towels and bed sheets are provided. The bedroom to rent can host 2 persons. You have access to: living room, bathroom, and
neighborhood_overview: International and familial neighborhood (near UNESCO): Immediately nearby: - Metro station (highly appreciated after nighty jaunts), - Minimarket open until 20h30, and another one open until 00h00 (5 min)! - Japaneese fine pâtisserie, - Many exotic restaurants (Indian, Italian, Korean, Lebanese, Thai,...). - Run for jogging along the best sights of Paris: Avenue de Breteuil (Invalides) or Champs de Mars (Tour Eiffel), - Have a swim at 5 min (Piscine Blomet), - Have pic-nic in front of the Invalides, - Have a pint of beer at one of the cheapest and trendiest bars of Paris (5 min), - Taste saucisson or cheese at the market on next avenue (Avenue de Saxe), on Saturday mornings.
transit: Metro lines: 10 (0 min walking), 6, 12, 13 (7 min walking), 8 (10 min walking). Bicycles available at self-service station (Vélib) just round the corner! Bus stop: "Sèvres-Lecourbe" on bus lines: - Line 39 (Issy -> Musée du Louvre -> Gare du Nord) - Line 70 (Radio-France -> St-Germain-des-Prés -> Hôtel-de-Ville) - Line 89 (Vanves Malakoff -> Luxembourg -> Porte de France)
access: You have access to: living room, bathroom, and your bedroom.
interaction: My guests are in holidays, so I let them interact as they wish. But I really appreciate any walk, drink or food, it can be lot of fun!! ;-) I am used to give general tips to enjoy the city, but if you have special wishes for activities or hangouts, I will search and tell you. ;-)
house_rules: No smoking inside, but possibly in the corridor, at the window.
host_about:
Bonjour et bienvenue à Paris !!

I'm Quentin, I am 24 years old, and I have lived in Paris for 1,5 year now. 

I really like Paris for its possibility to meet incredible people everywhere or to discover fabulous places everywhere. It's fantastic! Then, I'm persuaded that the best way to know and enjoy Paris is walking.

For traveling, I'm quite independent: I like to balance shared moments with my hosts and self discovery of the city. I enjoy walking or biking and try to get close to the typical local life.

Cities I can't forget: Barcelona, Grenoble, Liège (Belgium), Oporto, Cordoba (Spain),  Amsterdam, Aix-en-Provence...
I also visited or lived in: Lyon, Tours, Montpellier, Béziers, Bruxelles, Strasbourg, Genève, Bordeaux, Lille, London...
My next French destinations should be Nantes or Marseille!
street: Invalides - Ecole Militaire, Paris, Île-de-France 75015, France

space: Looking for Denver hotels? Consider our bed and breakfast Denver suite! This space is on the classic third floor of a house built in 1889. Entrance is private from the ground floor. The bed is full sized and comfortably sleeps two. There is a claw foot bathtub with shower in the bathroom that is shared only occasionally when the front office is being used during weekday, daytime hours. There is a blow dryer with shampoo, conditioner, soap and lotion.  Seating area with couch and roll-top desk.  Kitchen includes sink, coffee pot, hot pot for tea, cube refrigerator, small table and microwave.   The floor is carpeted and walls freshly painted.  Lots of light during the day. Air conditioner and fans in case of hot weather.  Steam radiators in the winter. Price includes local taxes of 14.75%. Although our house is on a busy street, the house is quiet in a tree-lined,  historic neighborhood.  Our next door neighbor is a church across the alley.  Parking with no time restriction is available

host_about: I have lived and worked very happily in my house for 21 years.  It is just recently that I have decided to create spaces to share with visitors.  I work as a Jungian psychotherapist in an office on the 3rd floor. So, during the week there will be a few people sharing the bathroom and waiting room that are part of the 3rd floor suite.  Otherwise, you will have private access to the entire floor. Our 2nd floor unit is a 950 sq.ft private apartment with a well-stocked kitchen, a formal dining room, large living room with deck and a bath & bedroom behind French Doors.  There is also a pull-out full size couch/bed in the living room and an Aero bed that can be moved wherever might be convenient for the 5th guest. The mattresses are Tempurpedic on both floors. I have a Samoyed named Bud who keeps all of us safe and smiling.  He has a space in the front yard and stays on the first floor with me.  When I recently traveled to Marseilles, France, I had the great good fortune to stay in a local home and learned first-hand how great it is to have a personal connection away from home. I have also been to South Africa, Botswana and Zimbabwe as well as Mexico and Costa Rica. I love meeting new people and seeing the world both first hand and through the eyes of my guests who bring their stories.  Our many Airbnb guests bring the world to us.

neighborhood_overview: Le quartier de Saint-Gilles est un quartier à la fois bobo et populaire, très dynamique et authentique. Côté populaire, la place Bethléem juste à côté est parfaite pour un repas ou café au soleil tout en profitant de l'ambiance et des fréquentes animations durant l'été. Le Parvis de Saint-Gilles à 5 mn à pied est aussi un lieu de vie très agréable avec un marché tous les matins et plein de cafés ou restaurants branchés. La Grand Place et les principaux centres d'intérêt de Bruxelles-Ville sont accessibles en moins de 30 mn à pied et très facilement en transports en commun. Le tram 81 juste en bas de l'immeuble vous emmène en 20 mn dans le quartier chic d'Ixelles pour du shopping rue du Bailly, une visite du musée Horta aux châtelains ou une bière autour Dr la place flagey.
transit: Le logement se trouve à moins de 10 mn à pied de la gare du midi, terminus des navettes provenant de Charleroi et arrêt des trains provenant de Zaventem. Il est possible de se garer dans les rues alentours.

If you're planning to host me, there shouldn't be any trouble neither, cause I'm actually like Belgian people! ;)

See you soon!

Chloé

Wisdom says "You can't make everybody happy all of the time", but I try anyway...
Interests:
Yoga, Tai Chi, Reading, Writing, Movies, Apple picking (24 harvests around the world I love Nature and I love Autumn and I rather stay in shape like this versus going to a gym), Cycling,Gardening, Picnics, Quality time with my kids.

Zorba the Greek, All the books of Louis de Bernieres, Guliver's Travels, The Hitch Hiker's guide to the Galaxy, All the books of Angela Carter.

neighborhood_overview: Charmant quartier/village typiquement parisien. Vous gôuterez les cuisines du monde dans les nombreux restaurants de la rue Daguerre,  en partie piétonne, ( Le Daguerrotype, film d'Agnès Varda) et les petites rues adjacentes. Terrasses au soleil, bars et commerces, boutiques de créateurs, marchés bio, cinémas et théâtres de Montparnasse. Parcs à proximité : Jardin du Luxembourg et Parc Montsouris. Un des quartiers de Paris les plus appréciés  par les touristes ! et par les parisiens car très safe la nuit et très proche de tout.
notes: En réponse à des questions courantes : les draps et serviettes de bain sont fournies. La cuisine est équipée de tous les ustensiles nécessaires. Le quartier est très safe et calme, on peut rentrer le soir à pied  sans aucun problème. Le dimanche, ma rue et les rues adjacentes deviennent piétonnes.
transit: Transports directs pour les lieux réputés : St Germain des Prés, Musée d'Orsay, Notre Dame, Le Louvre, Tour Eiffel, Pompidou/Beaubourg : Métro Denfert-Rochereau ligne 4,6, Métro Gaité ligne 13. Bus direct pour l'aéroport d'Orly, Train RER B pour l'aéroport Roissy Charles de Gaulle. Accès en 10mn à pied à la gare Montparnasse (Château de Versailles). 10mn de l'autouroute du Sud A1. Parking facile dans les rues avoisinantes.
access: Les voyageurs auront accès à Internet (WIFI), à la télévision, radio, lecteur CD et  DVD. Ils seront totalement indépendants. Aucun partage d'équipements ou de zones de  logement.
interaction: Le jour de leur arrivée, je leur explique le fonctionnement de tous les équipements.  Je prends le temps de  répondre à  leurs questions : transports, lieux à visiter, évènements culturels, bons restos, puis je les quitte en laissant le lieu entièrement à leur disposition pendant tout le séjour avec un contact à joindre si moi-même je ne reste pas à Paris. Ils ont évidemment mes coordonnées téléphoniques et e-mail.
house_rules: J'attends qu'ils respectent le bon état de l'appartement, qu'ils ne fassent pas de bruit fort après 10h du soir pour les voisins. Je n'autorise pas les animaux.  Le logement est non fumeur.
host_about: Etudiante en art dans les années 80,  j'ai loué un studio de 22m2 dans ce petit quartier du 14ème que j'adore. Je l'ai acheté, puis celui d'à coté. Devenant maman et vivant en famille j'ai acquis les combles et nous avons recréé l'espace que vous découvrirez en restant ici.  Ce qui m'importe c'est que vous vous sentiez chez moi comme chez vous,  et que vous ayez un coup de foudre pour ce charmant petit coin de Paris. Agnès Varda l'a immortalisé  avec son documentaire "Le Daguerrotype" . J'adore voir des films en salle :  ici c'est idéal grâce aux nombreux cinémas,  et théâtres. J'adore la présence du vert en ville: deux très beaux jardins, le Luxembourg et le parc Montsouris et même le beau cimetière de Montparnasse. Bienvenue, et très bon séjour chez moi!

host_about:
Born in Bordeaux, I’ve been living in Paris for 7 years.
After attending business school in Marseille, I’ve started working for Synomia agency, where I deal with digital strategy.
I love travelling (Cuba, Reunion island, Thailand, Colombia, Australia,…) and sports (soccer, tennis, skying). I am fluent in English and Spanish.
Since one year I’m living in the flat in 11th quartier in Paris with my housemate Kevin.
Since both of us love travelling around, we decided to rent the flat while we are not there.

Bordelais d'origine, j'habite à Paris depuis 7 ans.
Après des études de commerces à Marseille, j'ai commencé à travailler pour l'agence Synomia en m'occupant de Stratégie digitale.
J'aime voyager (Cuba, Réunion, Thaïlande, Colombie, Australie, .......),  je parle couramment anglais et espagnol et je pratique du sport (foot, tennis, sky).
Depuis 1 an je vis dans cet appartement situé dans le onzième arrondissement de Paris avec mon colocataire Kevin.
Tous les deux aimant les voyages, nous avons décidé de louer l'appartement pour les semaines où nous ne sommes pas là.

Nato a Bordeaux, vivo a Parigi ormai da 7 anni.
Dopo aver concluso l’Università di Economia a Marsiglia, ho iniziato a lavorare per l’agenzia Synomia, dove tutt’ora mi occupo di “big data”.
Mi piace viaggiare (Cuba, Riunione, Tailandia, Colombia, Australia,…) e praticare sport (calcio, tennis, sci). Ho un buon livello di inglese e spagnolo.
Da un anno vivo nell’appartamento che vi propongo, situato nell’undicesimo distretto di Parigi, assieme al mio coinquilino Kevin.
Entrambi appassionati di viaggi, abbiamo deciso di affittare l’appartamento in nostra assenza.

host_about:
Bonjour, je m’appelle Romain ! 

Ayant été hôte sur Airbnb à Marseille avec succès, j’ai appris à connaître les attentes des hôtes et des voyageurs. Je suis également passionné par le secteur tourisme et possède des expériences marquantes en locations touristiques. 

De nature entrepreneur, j’ai créé Renty. Renty c’est le premier label à travers Airbnb qui assure les voyageurs d’une qualité élevée et de services hauts de gamme. Cela vous permet, en tant que voyageur, de bénéficier d’un panier accueil, de produits d’hygiène, d’informations touristiques, d’une assistance téléphonique 7j/7 de 9h à 22h. 

Renty permet également de faciliter la vie aux hôtes en gérant à leur place leur activité sur Airbnb. Il n’est en effet pas toujours simple pour eux de concilier la gestion de cette activité et leur vie professionnelle, leur vie personnelle, leurs loisirs, … 

Renty, c’est également des services ponctuels et de dépannage pour les hôtes occasionnels ou ne louant qu’une partie de leur logement. 

N’hésitez pas à me contacter pour plus d’informations sur mon activité, je serai heureux d’y répondre !

La découverte d'autres pays, d'autres lieux proches ou lointains me réjouit toujours autant. 
Ce quartier du chemin vert : un vrai bonheur, un authentique quartier parisien. Ses habitants, ses commerçants sont d'une gentillesse et d'une serviabilité remarquables.

name: 4 pièces Paris -Nation/Gare de Lyon
summary: Ce 4 pièces refait à neuf très lumineux et très calme, se situe entre Nation et Gare de Lyon. Il a vue sur la Promenade Plantée qui permet de rejoindre le centre de Paris (Bastille) par une jolie ballade. Idéal pour 6 personnes 20€ de plus par personne et par nuit au-delà de 6 personnes
space: L'appartement de 83m2 est située au 7ème et dernier étage (avec ascenseur) avec un petit balcon fleuri sur lequel est installé une petite table et deux chaises. Il est très ensoleillé et très calme, donnant sur une cour, une rue très peu fréquentée et la Promenade Plantée. L'appartement est composé de : - 1 chambre parentale avec un lit double - 1 chambre d'enfant avec 2 lits simples superposés - 1 chambre d'amis avec un lit double et un lit bébé possible - 1 grand salon avec un canapé convertible 2 places confortable - 1 salle de bain (avec toilettes) et 1 salle d'eau - Toilettes séparés - 1 cuisine toute équipée (dont lave-vaisselle, lave-linge, four, micro-ondes, machine à café nespresso, grille-pain etc...) - 1 bar qui sépare la salle à manger et le salon - 1 table pour 8 personnes dans la salle à manger - 1 grande table basse  Nous avons tout le nécessaire pour bébé et enfant (jeux, transat, baignoires etc...).

neighborhood_overview: Quartier calme et familial très proche du Bois de Vincennes, bien situé car il est très facile de rejoindre le centre de Paris et les quartiers du Marais, de Bastille notamment. Beaucoup de petits restaurants de qualité autour de chez nous, que nous serons ravis de vous conseiller.
transit: L'appartement est à côté du Métro Bel-Air (ligne 6 qui permet de rejoindre la ligne 14 en 3 arrêts), et à 5 minutes à pied du Métro Michel Bizot (ligne 8). La place de la Nation est situé à 15 minutes à pied ou 2 arrêts de métro en ligne 6 et est très bien desservie (RER A, lignes de métro 1, 2, 6 et 9). De nombreux bus permettent de rejoindre divers endroits de Paris (29 pour Bastille et le Marais, 46 pour République).
access: Nous mettons à disposition bien entendu de nos hôtes toute la vaisselle que nous avons, ainsi que la TV et Internet (WIFI).  Également pour vous si nécessaire : le lave-vaisselle, le lave-linge et le sèche-linge !
house_rules: Logement non-fumeur. Par contre, notre petit balcon accueillera avec plaisir nos amis les fumeurs !
host_about:
Nous avons tous les deux 30 ans et vivons à Paris depuis 10 ans mais venons chacun d'une région de France différente : Laurent de Haute-Savoie et moi de Marseille.

Nous aimons beaucoup voyager, que ce soit pour partir dans les belles régions françaises dans lesquelles nos familles habitent ou pour un voyage à l'étranger (un par an c'est le minimum vital) ! 
La découverte d'autres régions et d'autres pays a toujours fait partie de notre vie : mon père est d'origine arménienne et ma mère d'origine italienne, j'ai vécu 6 mois aux Etats-Unis et Laurent a, quant à lui, vécu 6 mois en nouvelle-Zélande.

Ce qui est important pour nous lors de nos voyages, c'est de se sentir bien alors avoir un logement confortable et chaleureux, ça fait partie du voyage, surtout depuis que nous avons deux enfants !

A bientôt j'espère

host_about:
Hi Everyone,
I'm Anne-Marie, French expat in Sydney. Originally from Marseille in Provence, I spent 4 years in Paris and 5 in London before moving down under.
One of my biggest passions is travelling, my biggest highlights being Iceland, Italy, Vietnam, Japan, and of course Australia.
I am also a music lover, with a penchant for rock, metal, classical music and Scandinavian music.
I love hosting friends and family and enjoy making them comfortable and at home. I am also a house proud person as you can probably tell from my apartment's pictures: I like living in a pretty, simple, clean and tidy environment. I live in this apartment with my lovely husband.

name: Midcentury Studio Close to Downtown
summary: Wake up to the heart of Seattle in this cozy midcentury modern urban hideaway. Minutes away from museums and Capitol Hill; just around the corner from the airport light rail. Complementary Stumptown coffee, toiletries + all the books you can read!
space: I take great pride in my little urban abode and have furnished it with midcentury modern and Danish design. Having spent years abroad, the flat is filled with art, foreign language books and art books. There is a Queen size bed in the bedroom nook with 500 thread count sheets and a full-length couch for additional guests. Towels and extra sheets are provided.  While I do have all the mod-cons (high-speed WiFi, flat screen TV, DVD player, toaster, etc). I try to keep the space tranquil and without too many electronic distractions. There is a bluetooth Jawbone speaker so you can play music in any room from your smart phone. This is a wonderful older building with tons of character. There is an elevator and wheelchair access at the basement floor. I have lived in Seattle for a long time (not including my years in Europe and elsewhere), so I am happy to provide tips for whatever you are looking to do or try!

neighborhood_overview: The First Hill / Capitol Hill area is renown for its vibrant culture, bars, museums, and underground spaces. My apartment is near two excellent art/cocktail bars and the Frye art museum (Free). The nearby luxury Sorrento hotel features stately dining and a classic brass-ring bar and fireplace. There are multiple late-night convenience stores in a 5 minute walking radius, as well as hospitals for any medical needs. You are a 5 minute walk to Pike Street and 10 minute walk to the heart of Capitol Hill (Pike and Broadway: Neumos, The Comet, Cha Cha, etc.) The area is well-lit and relatively quiet, despite being so close to downtown.
notes: No microwave.
transit: There is limited on-street parking; it is advisable to take public transport, Uber, bike, or walk.  Getting to/from the airport:  Just take the Link light rail from SEA to downtown Seattle; get off at the Union station or Westlake station in the downtown underground tunnel and walk/Uber/taxi to the apartment. Link costs 3 one way and takes about 35min.  It is 15 minutes walking to the apartment from Westlake Tunnel station or University Street Tunnel station. You can also get a taxi using: Orange Cab - (phone number hidden)  Yellow Cab - (phone number hidden) The apartment is near Metro bus routes #2, 12, 60 (and for longer routes, 193 and 309).   It is 10 minutes walking to the Convention Place tunnel station For bikers: There is a cheap bike renting program, with a station 5 min walking away at the Frye museum: (website hidden) (8/24hrs, 16/72hrs).  Check out (website hidden) to map out the safest paths. Distance-wise, you are: 5 minutes walking to Pike/Pine core of the hip Capito
host_about:
Formerly an expat in Marseille, I've recently moved back to Seattle, USA. I work in marketing data, but am passionate about the social sciences and social justice. 

I'm a low-key traveler and a passionate host. I'm kind of obsessed with little details. For instance, if you come stay with me, I'll provide you with 4 ways to make your coffee (drip, ceramic pourover, french press, and chemex).

I love giving tips and welcoming people into my home. When abroad, I prefer local markets and staying in off-the-beaten-track neighborhoods where I can really get the spirit of the place. I also like to travel with a purpose: to visit friends, to do something, to learn something. 

Since I'm a francophile (lived in France for three years), you can imagine I'm a fan of wine, books, and long conversation.

When time allows, I go out dancing Swing, seeing theatre or modern dance, bike riding, seeing shows, or playing my violin. 

But I never start a day without reading the New York Times.
street: Boren Avenue, Seattle, WA 98104, United States

space: The flat has a real wow factor - high ceilings, wooden floors and bare brick fireplace with wood burning stove. The kitchen is really well equipped (I used to work in a kitchen utensil shop!) and we will leave all the basic spices, oils etc for your use. The living room has a giant sofa (can be used as a sofa bed), dining space and TV.  We have Virgin tv with lots of channels. The south-facing terrace is a real sun trap.  It overlooks the neighbours' gardens and isn't overlooked itself.   The bathroom is modern with a great shower over the bath.  Our bedroom is at the back of the house overlooking the gardens.  It has a comfy double bed and some built in storage. Everything is white - it's super serene and calming.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is perfectly located in the east center of Paris. A very good mix of residential buildings and shops. The area is peaceful (but not asleep) and is very well connected. The flat is just a few steps from Gare de Lyon train station, 5 minutes walk from Ledru-Rollin and 10 minutes walk from Bastille and Le Marais.  Very close, you will also find the "Coulée Verte", an elevated planted promenade (always a nice walk and a cool spot for runners) and just behind, the famous Aligre market, opened 6 days per week, where you can taste the best of french gastronomy.   On the other side of the Seine, you can stroll in the lovely "Jardin des Plantes" (botanical gardens), visit the National Museum of Natural History and even a little zoo.   All the area is full of good restaurants and cosy places to enjoy a glass of wine or a cocktail.
transit: From Gare de Lyon, you can easily go everywhere in Paris and even further. - Taxis are always waiting close to the station.  - Subway lines 1, 14 and 5 are just a few steps from the flat. You can also find a lot of bus lines (very useful to go to Quartier Latin, Saint-Germain-des-Prés and Montparnasse areas) and RER lines A & D. - Several Velib (public bicycles) stations are surrounding the area. - Obviously, Gare de Lyon is also the gate to the south of France. With TGV, the trip takes only 2H to reach Lyon and 3H30 for Marseille.
access: A luminous and spacious bedroom (18 m2 or 194 ft2), with private balcony and space in the dressing. Charming queen size bed, design desk & MP3 dock. Free access to the Living-room / library and the fully equipped kitchen (with oven, hotplates, SMEG fridge & freezer, washing machine, dishwasher, teapot and Nespresso machine).  Shared bathroom with a bathtub.
interaction: I speak french, english and a bit spanish, I would be glad to help you before and during your stay, by giving you some tips about the city and the good places of the neighborhood.

Whenever I am traveling and I am not in Paris I am open to share my home with people that want to enjoy the wonders of this vibrant and cosmopolitan city, while staying in a peaceful and comfortable environment.

If you are easy-going and respectful, and if you are looking for calm and harmonious flats, then my home is the perfect accomodations for you!
