I am a Sydney Girl living by the Beach with Carlos. I own a vegetarian/vegan restaurant called The Dandylion Bondi. English is my mother tongue, and I also speak basic French. I am 32 years old, and I live 5 mins walk from beautiful Bondi Beach.

I love traveling, especially in nature! Some of my favorite places are the Dead Sea in Israel, Rishikesh in India, and the Calanques in Marseille. Outside of Australia, I have lived in New York, Paris and India. My favorite cities outside of Sydney are Paris, San Fransico & Munich. 

Other interests I have are diving, tennis, horse riding, krav maga, and general adventures. I also do photography/videography and retouching - formerly fashion/doco stuff but now it's mainly food related ☺️. I am a people person, and love to meet new and exciting people with a passion for life. I am quite a clean person, and very chilled in general.

space: This is a full height half/basement suite in a "Vancouver Special", a ubiquitous architectural style from the mid-60s to mid-80s, now prized for its spaciousness and versatility.  Our suite has large windows in every room, south and west facing in the open concept living/dining room open to the fully equipped kitchen (stove, microwave, fridge, dishwasher, toaster, kettle, coffee maker, pots and pans, dishes, glasses and cutlery for 8, basic spices, herbs, tea and coffee).  Two bedrooms have a queen size bed and two bedrooms have a double bed.  A single bed can be added to one bedroom with a double bed. The main bath has a tub and shower combination, as well as  a front loading washer and dryer.  There is a second separate powder room.

neighborhood_overview: Langara is central to almost every other neighbourhood in Vancouver.  The 49th Avenue station of the Canada Line (ALRT) will take you downtown(Pacific Centre, Gastown, Yaletown, West End)  in 14 minutes and to the YVR in 12 minutes. UBC is 25 minutes via 49UBC, Metrotown Shopping Centre 15 minutes, and Chinatown 20 minutes away via 3Main.  Walk to the Langara YMCA, the 2.7km perimeter path around Langara Golf Course, Sunset Community Centre,  tennis courts (at 55th Avenue) Queen Elizabeth Park (second largest after Stanley Park, 130 acre aboretum in a former stone quarry, highest point in Vancouver, providing fantastic views of the north shore mountains, Mt Baker on a clear day, SFU, and the gulf islands to the south), Oakridge Shopping Mall, and numerous parks within a 10 block radius.  The Ontario St bike path is a stone's throw away, and you can ride to Science World in the Olympic Village in 15 minutes. Westward on the seawall at Science World is Granville Island, Kits Point, Point
notes: This 4BR suite is one of two suites in the house.  The upstairs suite is occupied by family  - a couple plus their toddler.
transit: A myriad of public transit options abound.   1. Canada Line at 49th Avenue goes to YVR directly in 12 minutes and downtown in 15 minutes.   2. Bus routes on 49th Ave, Main St and Cambie St will take you north to downtown/Stanley Park, west to UBC, Kerrisdale and Kitsilano, north along Main St to hip craft brew pubs and restaurants (sushi, french, african, thai, all day breakfast diners, dim sum to name a few), one of kind clothing shops and east to Metrotown Mall. Other options: 3. Designated Bike Routes - closest is Ontario St, running north to downtown and south to Marine Drive, which will take you to Richmond via the Canada Line Bridge (pedestrian and cycling lane below the train itself). We can recommend bike rental shops nearby, or near the seawall, Granville Island and downtown-Stanley Park.   4. Car Share companies - Car2Go, Zipcar, Evo and Modo.  5. There is parking for one car in the back yard and limited street parking is available.  Because of our proximity to Langara Colleg
access: The suite is self-contained, with a front door entrance.  An outdoor patio table, chairs and umbrella are available for your use also.
interaction: We hosted international homestay students for 10 years and enjoyed  sharing our knowledge and love of Vancouver with guests, as well as making lasting friends from Asia, South America and Europe.  Christian was transplanted from France 40+ years ago, about the same time as Meelie emigrated from Saskatchewan (no relation to Jimmy Pattison).  Christian is an avid cyclist, Meelie a recreational cyclist and powerwalker, and share a love of cooking, food, wine, craft beer and single malts.  We can provide cycling and road maps, recommendations for local places to eat and drink,(al fresco with service - QE Park, Jericho Sailing Club, Provence Marinaside, Joe Fortes), kayak, hike, people watch, entertain children or your inner child, and live like a local. We are only a 5 minute drive away if needed, and are also reachable by mobile/text/email.
house_rules: House rules: We hope you will make yourself at home and enjoy your stay! We enjoy cordial relations with our neighbours and our upstairs tenant, so the only rules are related to being good neighbours: 1. No smoking (of any kind) please.  This is a non-smoking house. 2. No shoes inside. Please remove your shoes inside the suite.  The floors are wood and tile, and slippers or socks will not only make cleaning easier, it will be quieter. 3. This is a quiet residential neighbourhood, with tenants in the upstairs suite (who don't wear shoes indoors or smoke).  Please keep noise levels to a respectful and reasonable level, especially after 10PM, inside and outdoors, to respect our tenants' and our neighbours' right to quiet enjoyment of their indoor and outdoor spaces.  4. No parties or additional overnight guests other than those registered in your reservation, please. 5. Please use the recycling and compost containers which are provided.
host_about:
My husband Christian emigrated from France 40+ years ago, and I from Saskatchewan(LOL).   We love food and wine. He is an avid cyclist; I am a recreational one.  We took our first separate vacation(s) in 2013; I took our daughters then aged 16 and 19 to NYC staying in our first airbnb in the Lower East Side.  He went on a cycling vacation with friends to Tucson, Arizona.  For 18 years we spent two weeks in the summer cycling as a family in Whistler, renting the same cabin (pre-airbnb)and for the past 14 years Christian and I have made an annual pilgrimage in June to Yellow Point Lodge on Vancouver Island, which is a summer camp for adults (no children or pets allowed, and NO internet reception!) At YPL we practise the triathlon of eat/read/sleep/repeat interspersed with cycling the country roads, kayaking, using the tree shower on warm days, and exploring the forest. 

Our most recent airbnb stays were in 2014 in Marseille, the Dordogne, and Brittany. Local bread, cheese, wine, foie gras, oysters and other shellfish = epicureal bliss.

My dream is to run a B&B in France (or the Okanagan), where Christian could organize cycling tours for people who love food and drink as much as we do. 

The novel I most enjoyed recently was All the Light We Cannot See.  I love NYC for the Brooklyn Bridge, the Staten Island ferry, TKTS, the museums, LES,the Tenement Museum,Magnolia Bakery. I love Portland for its food, craft beer, bike routes, parks, and Powell's Books. I love Seattle for its Zoo, Science Centre, SAM, Dale Chiuly (OK, Tacoma) great restaurants and great selection of wine and beer - my favourite weekend getaway, except for the exorbitant cost of parking downtown.  I love my neighbourhood of Riley Park, just off Main St. I am hooked on Netflix.

Because we prefer to stay in a pied-a-terre(airbnb or VRBO) instead of a hotel while travelling for more than a weekend, and because we loved hosting homestay students for 10 years, we have decided to take the plunge and become airbnb hosts ourselves, now that our daughters have left home and we are empty nesters.

Parisienne de naissance, j'ai passé de nombreuses années à l'étranger (Angleterre, Allemagne et Italie) et adore recevoir des gens de tous horizons. Etant guide à Paris, je pourrais vous donner quelques renseignements utiles pour agrémenter votre séjour parisien. This houseboat is an exciting  novelty for me and I really want to share my enthusiasm of living on the water in the heart of the city as well as my knowledge of the city with anyone who likes to discover cities differently. I also happen to be a guide and can show you round if you want.

name: Green Powered Cozy Apartment
space: Situated right next to the St. Martin Canal (20m away), the apartment is in the heart of one of the trendiest neighborhoods in Paris.  The apartment is a spacious 33sqm studio on the 3rd floor of a traditional 19th century building. The interior is a colorful, tasteful blend of vintage French and modern furniture. The main room has a comfortable, double bed and a living area with sofa, armchair and dining-room table. The kitchen is separated from the living area by a small hallway and a door, and fully equipped with kitchen appliances and all pantry items. The apartment building and studio embody the charm of Paris, from the pre-Haussman architecture that defines former industrial areas of Paris to  the subtle scent of baking bread wafting up from the bakery below to the old, wooden staircase that leads you up to the apartment. The apartment is green powered with 100% renewable non fossile fuel energies from Enercoop, a socially responsible and non lucrative cooperative. Building acces

neighborhood_overview: The First Hill / Capitol Hill area is renown for its vibrant culture, bars, museums, and underground spaces. My apartment is near two excellent art/cocktail bars and the Frye art museum (Free). The nearby luxury Sorrento hotel features stately dining and a classic brass-ring bar and fireplace. There are multiple late-night convenience stores in a 5 minute walking radius, as well as hospitals for any medical needs.
notes: Please no guests other than those indicated on the reservation.  I don't have a land line or microwave. Sorry, but this apartment is not well suited to kids.
transit: There is limited on-street parking; it is advisable to take public transport, Uber, bike, or walk.  The apartment is near bus routes #2, 12, 60 (and for longer routes, 193 and 309).   It is 10 minutes walking to the Convention Place tunnel station It is 15 minutes walking to the Westlake Tunnel station or Union Street Tunnel station (where you can catch the Light Rail to the airport) Distance-wise, you are: 5 minutes walking to Pike/Pine core of the hip Capitol Hill area 10 minutes walking to the Downtown shopping center 20 minutes walking to the International/Chinatown district 15 minutes walking to the Central District
host_about:
Formerly an expat in Marseille, I've recently moved back to Seattle, USA. I work in marketing data, but am passionate about the social sciences and social justice. 

I'm a low-key traveler and a passionate host. I'm kind of obsessed with little details. For instance, if you come stay with me, I'll provide you with 4 ways to make your coffee (drip, ceramic pourover, french press, and chemex).

I love giving tips and welcoming people into my home. When abroad, I prefer local markets and staying in off-the-beaten-track neighborhoods where I can really get the spirit of the place. I also like to travel with a purpose: to visit friends, to do something, to learn something. 

Since I'm a francophile (lived in France for three years), you can imagine I'm a fan of wine, books, and long conversation.

When time allows, I go out dancing Swing, seeing theatre or modern dance, bike riding, seeing shows, or playing my violin. 

But I never start a day without reading the New York Times.

We want keep travelling from time to time either via real travel or hosting people from all over the world! We have both always been in love with this south of France city!

space: In being full of plants and paintings the apartment has a real home feel, plus it has the added cachet of having its own large private terrace. Nous avons pleins de choses à vous raconter tant sur notre périple pour venir s'installer, sur la vie des français au Québec, sur nos passions (moto, voiture, voyage, bonne bouffe, lézard et j'en passe). 

Pour ma part j'ai toujours grandi dans une maison pleine de vie, des amis qui s'invitent à la dernière minute pour manger ou dormir, des anniversaires en famille ou entre amis. Cela me manque, alors venez nous voir et nous enrichir de votre personne.

We have many things to tell you so much about our trip to come and settle, on the life of French in Quebec, our passions (motorcycle, car, travel, good food, lizard and so on).

For my part I have always grown up in a house full of life, friends who invite themselves at the last minute to eat or sleep, birthdays with family or friends. I miss it, so come see us and enrich us about your person.

This fits two people; either a couple in the bedroom or two friends - one in the bedroom and the other on the fold down futon.  ***If you are expecting an additional person and want to ask, please do not spring this on my at my front door.***

neighborhood_overview: We live close to a train crossing.  I had this in the house manual, but apparently most people don't read it.  If you are super sensitive to noises, maybe this isn't the spot.  Please remember this is a city! The St. Claude Arts District  hosts an art walk of the local galleries the 2nd Saturday of each month.  There are now many spots to eat & drink in the neighborhood and I have a guide book in the house with addresses.
notes: If you are highly (I mean extreme) allergic to animals, this may not be the right house for you.  While there are NO pets allowed in the apartment, there are cats that hang on the porch and I have a dog.  I may carry traces of dander (on me) into the apartment when I clean and I cannot guarantee a perfectly hypoallergenic environment. There is also a train nearby, a neighbor's rooster, and a church bell.  If you are highly sensitive to noise, you might want to find a spot further from the train and the church.  (I don't even hear these things anymore.)  Brett & I work very hard between every guest to make it as close to perfect as possible.  While we want you to feel at home, please treat the apartment with respect.  If you are looking for a hotel atmosphere with a maid, please do not book my place. Check in is anytime after 3:00 p.m. and check out is at 11:00 a.m. unless special arrangements are made.  If you have a later flight and need to stow your bags at my place, we can arrange t
transit: There are two bus lines close to the house that can take you down to the French Quarter.  The 5 is on Royal Street and the 55 on St. Claude Ave.  There is a map on (URL HIDDEN) to plan any trip.  Most people walk, since it is only 1 mile to the edge of the French Quarter and takes about 15 minutes walking.

I have basic cable hooked up, so local news and weather is available.  There is Wifi at the house and at most coffee shops. Prices will be affected by festivals like Mardi Gras and Jazz Fest and the weekly rate dos NOT apply during these fes

host_about:
I am originally from Milwaukee and graduated from UWM with an Art degree.  I moved to New Orleans at the end of 2000 and fell in love with the city.  I worked freelance and for a contractor for almost 10 years painting furniture and interiors.  I am currently working with a bike tour company that shows people a different side of New Orleans. I am also teaching myself how to sew and upholster furniture.  I love suggesting places to eat, see music, and enjoy the sights. 

My 5 favorite cities that I've visited so far outside the USA:  Prague, Saint Petersburg, Milan, Amsterdam and San Miguel de Allende.  Favorites in USA:  New Orleans, Austin, Chicago, Portland, and Milwaukee.  Top 5 cities I hope to visit soon: Stockholm, London, Berlin, Marseille and Barcelona.

name: Attractive central canal-view apartment
summary: My house is situated in the Baarsjes, one of the most lively neighbourhoods of Amsterdam. It is very centrally located. Close by Rijksmuseum, van Goghmuseum, FOAM, Huis Marseille, Concertgebouw, AnneFrank Huis, Galleries, the Negen Straatjes, the Dam, EYE, Jordaan, Vondelpark and of course the Leidseplein. The bright and sunny house is located on a tree-lined  quiet street and overlooks the largest canal (actually a connecting point of two different canals) of Amsterdam.
space: This sunny and comfortable place (65m2) is not one in a dozen newly renonovated apartments. It is an authentic and warm house in which I happily live since ten years. In the morning the sun shines into the livingroom, sometimes projecting the moving water onto the beamed ceiling. In the afternoon it turns up in the kitchen which is perfect for long dinners and breakfast. A balcony facing the communal backyard can be entered both from the the kitchen and the bedroom. I don't own a television, but you're welcome to have a look at my books.

host_about:
Salut chers voyageurs!
Je suis Loris, je suis un jeune marseillais passionné de sport (particulièrement par le basket), de musique et de voyages! 
Je suis une personne qui savoure chaque instant et curieuse de découvrir le monde . Je suis enchanté par cette expérience de location sur Airbnb qui me permet de rencontrer des personnes ayant les mêmes centres d'intérêts et permettant un contact entre voyageurs des 4 coins du monde.
Je loue et m'occupe de biens immobiliers appartenant à ma famille et amis, et essaye de vous faire découvrir la région dès l'arrivée dans l'appartement.
En espérant que vous passerez de bons moments dans ces logements et dans cette merveilleuse région!

J'attend des voyageurs, exactement le même comportement que j'ai quand je suis voyageurs.  Je souhaite que vous laissiez l'appartement propre, rangé, dans le même état que vous le trouverez a votre arrivée, ne pas touchez a mes affaires (website hidden) pas fumez a l'intérieur. Enlevez les draps a votre départ. Merci
host_about:
Je suis originaire de Marseille.
J'ai un diplôme d'éducatrice spécialisée, j'ai exercé pendant 8 ans dans différents instituts, auprès de jeunes en difficultés, de jeunes enfants handicapés mentale et moteur. J'ai adoré ce métier. Je suis quelqu'un de très relationnelle.
Et puis petit à petit je me suis orientée vers la restauration, j'ai été directrice d'un restaurant pendant 4 ans .
Aujourd'hui je me suis lancée dans la grande aventure de mon propre restauration. Je travaille beaucoup, mais tous les jours passent et ne se ressemble pas.
Je rencontre des gens de tous milieux, avec toujours le même objectif:
Qu'ils passent un agréable moment dans mon restaurant.
J'aime le bon vin, découvrir de nouvelles saveurs, et surtout les bons repas entre amis.
Je suis une jeune fille dynamique, souriante, très accueillante, serviable, curieuse de tout et aimant les défis.

Quand j'ai du temps libre, je pratique du yoga, et du jogging.
Le sport a toujours fait partie de ma vie, ça me vide l'esprit et ça me permet de redonner de l'énergie.

Pour moi, être une bonne hôte, c'est être présente pour mes voyageurs, échanger avec eux, leur mode de vie, leur culture et pouvoir au mieux les renseigner et les guider dans la découverte de paris, qui est pour moi la plus belle ville aux monde.

name: Beautiful House close to Crouch End
summary: Spacious & very airy Victorian house built in 1889, in the centre of Crouch End, North London. Modern deco, stripped floors throughout, with garden and roof terrace. Overall bright and minimalist feel.
space: The house is very centrally located, just a 5 minute walk to Crouch End, where there are loads of independent shops, cafes and restaurants.  The house is bright and airy, painted in white throughout and with very high ceilings, so there is a great sense of space. The decor is modern and overall feels fairly minimal.
description: Spacious & very airy Victorian house built in 1889, in the centre of Crouch End, North London. Modern deco, stripped floors throughout, with garden and roof terrace. Overall bright and minimalist feel. The house is very centrally located, just a 5 minute walk to Crouch End, where there are loads of independent shops, cafes and restaurants.  The house is bright and airy, painted in white throughout and with very high ceilings, so there is a great sense of space. The decor is modern and overall feels fairly minimal. It is a large 4 bedroom house, although only 2 bedrooms are currently set up as bedrooms. The others are used as an office and for storage. There is therefore plenty of space, including a large living room, dining room, garden and roof terrace from the upstairs office.  Please note that I do not offer longer term rental (c. 2 weeks would be maximum). Crouch End is the sort of place that you would come to if you wanted to experience the less obvious side of the city.  In terms
neighborhood_overview: Crouch End is the sort of place that you would come to if you wanted to experience the less obvious side of the city.  In terms of who lives here, it is a mixture of young professionals and lots of families with kids, and has a real community feel - I know and am friendly with most of my neighbours, which apparently isn't a London trait (although we always spoke to our neighbours when I was growing up here!). It has a more off beat feel than much of London, I would say, and is full of charm, although I am obviously biased! In context, I'm the sort of person who prefers to stay in Park Slope than Manhattan, likes going to places like Marseille, San Sebastian and Berlin and I always try to avoid staying anywhere too obvious.  Even for Londoners, Crouch End is seen as tucked away and a little bit unknown and traditionally the area has always attracted a lot of creative people, especially musicians and actors. It's in zone 3, so not bang in the centre of town (thankfully), but has excellen
notes: I have two cats who are generally more likely to be outside than in - unless it is the thick of winter. They prefer not to travel, so please do not ask me to consider re-homing them.
transit: There is no metro/subway station - or 'tube' as we locals call it, but there is a bus stop less than 3 minutes' walk from the house which will take you to Finsbury Park Underground station. Alternatively, if you are happy to adopt a more leisurely pace, then you  can take a single bus directly into the centre of London (to Trafalgar Sq, via Kings Cross, and Covent Garden). Finsbury Park and Highgate tube stations are both within walking distance (20 mins brisk walk). More about the area, travel etc is detailed the Guidebook, but I also detailed local information at the house, which I have compiled, based on what I think is interesting to see/do/eat etc.
access: It is a large 4 bedroom house, although only 2 bedrooms are currently set up as bedrooms. The others are used as an office and for storage. There is therefore plenty of space, including a large living room, dining room, garden and roof terrace from the upstairs office.  Please note that I do not offer longer term rental (c. 2 weeks would be maximum).
interaction: I work from home most days, so am usually around, and can cook breakfast or at least have a cup of coffee with guests in the morning.

host_about:
Hello

I am in my late 30s and I work in advertising.

I live on my own in the house - with 2 moderately friendly cats - so there is plenty of space, which includes a big living room, sit-in kitchen and a dining room with a large table.

I also have an office with desk which I use occasionally if working from home but you are welcome to use this space.

Local to the area, I am a born and bred Londoner, so can offer lots of tips on the best places to go throughout the city and what to avoid!

Big fan of art, theatre, cinema, food, so I am happy to offer lots of advice on good things to see in town, if this interests you.

I studied French at university; donc, je sais parler français.

host_about:
My name is Sébastien and I am 46 years old. Originally, I am from the Massif Central, Clermont-Ferrand, major city of my region located in the middle of France.  
I have been living in Paris for 10 years in a row now. Previously, I lived in the French Capital from april 1999 to May 2002. 
I consider myself as a world citizen. I have been travelling around the world since I am 17. All in all, I visited around 45 countries and I have few friends abroad.
Through my work, everyday, I am in contact with colleagues from all over the world. 
Outside work, I have many activities or volunteer work. 
 I am a consul in a network named "Internations" dedicated to expatriates willing to meet foreigners and localsto get a glance at the french culture. I am organizing events to speak Spanish. 
I am fluent in English and I have good knowledges in Spanish. 
I am quite a sporty person as I am practising several sports on a regular basis such as golf, running, swimming and diving.
Having you as a guest in my place is opening you a door to the french culture and giving you the opportunity to stay in a lovely block with lots of restaurants. I can give you ideas of walks in Paris. I consider that the best way to visit Paris is either walking or taking the bus to see the most of it !!!

host_about:
FRANÇAIS (then ENGLISH)
Bonjour! 
Ravi de vous accueillir chez moi pendant votre séjour á Paris! 
J'ai pas mal voyagé sur tous les continents et vécu 3 ans au Perú: j'ai toujours aimé que l'on me fasse découvrir sa région, et j'adore aujourd'hui pouvoir faire découvrir la mienne (á Paris ou en Provence) aux ami-e-s du monde !! Je connais bien la ville et peut vous conseiller pas mal de chose, du tourisme classique au plus alternatif!
Vous verrez, le quartier de Ternes est très sympa, avec le fameux marché de la rue Poncelet (voir photos), une foule de restaurants de tous les horizons, et á deux pas de nombreux sites parisiens á connaitre (l'Arc de Triomphe, les Champs-Elysées, le Parc Monceaux, le Palais des Congrès, le Bois de Boulogne, etc...). De plus, on a rapidement accès á une foule de transports pour traverser la ville (ligne(URL HIDDEN)5mn, et á 10mn, RER A, lignes 1 et 6 ).
En ce qui me concerne, je suis un travailleur de la Solidarité Internationale (dans le « plaidoyer » c’est à dire les ONG qui conseillent/embêtent les gouvernements des pays développés pour une meilleure participation au développement des pays du Sud global) mais après 6 ans de bons et loyaux services en France et en Amérique Latine, je viens justement de reprendre un an d'étude á Paris. J'ai d'ailleurs aménagé mon chez moi pour m'y sentir bien durant les heures que j'y passe á réviser ou me détendre.. Vous apprécierez ce petit nid. 
Je suis très amateur de musique et de cinéma, j'ai donc un excellent système audio (ADAM A5X) pour écouter la musique, et un vidéoprojecteur, que vous etes évidemment bienvenu-e-s á utiliser pour aller au cinéma… tranquille chez soi ! 
Enfin, j'aime bien manger! Et la proximité du (très joli) marché Poncelet, oú l'on trouve vraiment les meilleurs produits du pays, est précieux pour les bons diners. La cuisine, très bien équipée, est á votre entière disposition. 
Si vous préférer manger dehors, vous trouverez dans le quartier une foule de très bons petits restaurants, du bons petit plats au menu gastronimque, je peux vous conseiller. Et n'oubliez pas de passer á la Boulangerie Niel, á 100m, qui est véritablement la meilleure du quartier ("de la ville" j'ai envie de dire.. mais j'ai des amis qui me le disputent...)
J'espère en tout cas que vous aimerez Paris et ses parisiens qui (étonnement ;) ont une sulfureuse réputation !!
Bon voyage et bienvenu-e-s ! 
reno

ENGLISH
Hello Hi,
Really happy to welcome you in my flat during your travel to Paris! :)

I have traveled pretty much on all continents including I lived 3 years in Perú: i have always liked having people making me discover their regions and i now like having people from the world discovering mine (in Paris ou in the south around Marseille)!
I know well Paris and can advise you on many things, from classical tourism to more alternative options.
You will see, Ternes area is really nice, with its famous farmers market in Poncelet street (see pictures) and a bunch of very diverse restaurants all around. You will find various touristical sites very close (Arc of Triomph, Champs Elysées, the amazing Monceaux Parc, the Palais des Congrès, Boulogne Hood, etc...). In addition, you have all key metro lines very close (ligne 2 and 3 within 5mn, and RER (express) A and ligne 1 and 6 à 10mn).

About me, I am working in international development (advocacy NGOs) but after years of work from Paris and from Latinamerica, I recently got back to paris in order to study during a year. That's why i have set up such a cosy space of life in my flat: to handle long hours of home work, and it works: I and people feel good at my place. :)
I love music and cinema, so i have a very good music system (ADAMX5) and a video projector that you are welcome to use: it 's really cool to be like at cinema... at home!
Lastly, I like good food. And the (very cute) market of Poncelet where you will find excellent farm and traditional product is really precious for good dinner. The kitchen is well equiped (oven, microwave, coffee maker, teepot, freezer etc....)
If you prefer to eat outside, you will find a lot of very good restaurants, from cute small places to serious gastronomic menus;i can advise you. And don't forget to give a try to the 100m away Boulangerie Niel (bakers and cake shop) that really is the best in the area ('of the city' i would actually say, but some friends would dispute that..) 

I really hope you will like Paris and its people who (surprisingly) have such a bad reputations!! ;)

Safe travel and welcome! 
Bon voyage et bienvenu-e-s !
reno

Bonjour, je m’appelle Romain ! 

Ayant été hôte sur Airbnb à Marseille avec succès, j’ai appris à connaître les attentes des hôtes et des voyageurs. Je suis également passionné par le secteur tourisme et possède des expériences marquantes en locations touristiques. 

De nature entrepreneur, j’ai créé Renty. Renty c’est le premier label à travers Airbnb qui assure les voyageurs d’une qualité élevée et de services hauts de gamme. Cela vous permet, en tant que voyageur, de bénéficier d’un panier accueil, de produits d’hygiène, d’informations touristiques, d’une assistance téléphonique 7j/7 de 9h à 22h. 

Renty permet également de faciliter la vie aux hôtes en gérant à leur place leur activité sur Airbnb. Il n’est en effet pas toujours simple pour eux de concilier la gestion de cette activité et leur vie professionnelle, leur vie personnelle, leurs loisirs, … 

Renty, c’est également des services ponctuels et de dépannage pour les hôtes occasionnels ou ne louant qu’une partie de leur logement. 

N’hésitez pas à me contacter pour plus d’informations sur mon activité, je serai heureux d’y répondre !

name: Abo's Abode in Montmartre
summary: This well-equipped, loft style apartment of 40 m2 (430 ft.2) is located in a calm garden courtyard, yet in the heart of a lively Montmartre neighborhood just a few minutes walk from the Sacre Coeur and all of Montmartre's numerous attractions.
space: The apartment is a loft-style, open space divided into three sections. The first part has a high quality pull-out couch bed, large closet with hangers and shelves for organizing your things and it can be closed off with curtains for privacy. The second part is the living area with a sofa that can be converted to a second bed, bookshelves and the contemporary Scandinavian design bathroom with shower, toilet and sink. The last section is a spacious, elevated, open kitchen flooded with light from the large windows and skylights. The kitchen is decorated in a country-style with rustic furniture, but is well equipped with modern conveniences: induction stove, oven/microwave, refrigerator, freezer, clothes washing machine, coffee maker, kettle, etc. It has everything you will need to prepare meals and be comfortable during your stay.

The kitchen is decorated in a country-style with rustic furniture, but is well equipped with modern conveniences: induction stove, oven/microwave, refrigerator, freezer, clothes washing machine, coffee maker, kettle, etc. I
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is a five minute walk from the Sacre Coeur and close to all of Montmartre's wonderful attractions - its picturesque staircases, windy cobblestone streets, spectacular views over Paris, galleries, museums, the Place du Tertre, Moulin Rouge and much more. It is also very close to the famous Porte de Clignancourt Flea market. The neighborhood is lively, authentic and convenient. Everything you should need is within a short walk from the apartment - cafes, bistros, restaurants, night spots, wine shops, boutiques, specialty shops, supermarkets, pharmacies, etc.
notes: Minimum stay of three nights
transit: The apartment is quickly and easily accessible from Charles de Gaulle and Orly airports by public transport or taxi. The apartment is only two stops on the metro from the Gare du Nord train station, where the Eurostar and TGV trains from London, Brussels and Amsterdam arrive, and it is also easily accessible from the Gare de l'Est, Gare de Lyon, Gare Saint Lazare and Gare Montparnasse train stations. There are several metro stations serving different lines and numerous bus stops within a few minutes walk of the apartment, making it easy and direct to get just about anywhere in Paris. For those coming by car, the apartment is just a short drive from the Peripherique (the Paris ring road) and easily accessible without getting bogged down in central Paris traffic.
access: Guests will have the entire well-equipped apartment to themselves and full use of all the amenities, including: washer, dryer, free high-speed wifi internet access and free, unlimited international phone calls to over 90 countries including the US, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, South Africa, all of Europe and many more. The apartment is located in a calm and beautiful courtyard garden full of trees, plants and flowers.
interaction: I am renting the apartment during an extended absence from Paris, but my friend Jeff who is American, has lived in the neighborhood for more than 20 years and speaks French fluently will meet you, show you the apartment and give you the keys. He will also be available to answer any questions you may have during your stay. You will also find lots of useful recommendations and information in the apartment.
house_rules: Be clean, respectful and enjoy your stay in Paris and the apartment.
host_about: I am a sound engineer originally from Marseilles, but I have been living in Paris for more than 25 years working with French television and various production companies. I also have a master's degree in Anthropology and have traveled extensively around the world. I enjoy meeting and engaging with people from all walks of life and discovering new places and cultures. I speak French and English fluently.

name: Central, calm & cosy 3 bedroom flat
summary: Cosy flat that comfortably fits 6 people, with comfy living room, 2or3 double BR (a dining room that can become a comfy double room)! 2min walk from pubs, shops, restaurants and buses stops, 15-25min walk from Princes Street and historic centre!
space: Our flat is really cosy and comfortable, suitable for a family or for friends. It has a separated kitchen with all the material and dishes you need (oven, microwave, blender, toaster...), one bathroom (with hairdryer), one living room with 2 comfortable coaches and a TV where you'll be able to relax after a full day of sightseeing or after enjoying the night in Edinburgh. You can also plan the next day with our guides/map in English and French and use our wireless access. The flat has one dining room with a big table (up to 6-7 people) and two rooms with double beds (we can add baby cot on demand). We have a supplementary double real mattress (very comfy, same than the beds' ones) that can be installed in one of the double room or in the dining room if you need it.  The flat is ideal for 4 to 6 people. neighborhood_overview: Our flat is situated on a really calm street, face to a little square-park where you can have a pic-nic or a barbecue with children games and ball field. You will find shops, stores, guide-recommended pubs and restaurants, art centre, less than 5 minutes walk from the door. 2 minutes walk from our door, you'll find buses stops towards every part of the city. It is really close (15 min walk/5 min cycle) from the centre of Leith which is a lovely and very typical Scottish area, where we love to go out for walks, drinks or dinner.  The flat has an ideal location to visit Edinburgh and all its treasures...
notes: Pet-free flat  We will accept booking with people with verified profile and with pictures. Do not hesitate to give us some details about your trip!
transit: We usually walk from/to the centre since Princes Street (New Town) is just 15 minutes from our flat. It will be 20-25 minutes walk to go to the Royal Mile to visit historic places (Edinburgh Castle, Holyrood palace...) and the National Museum of Scotland (Old Town).  Our flat is really convenient to access from the airport : the Airlink bus trip lasts 30 minutes from Airport to Waverley station and then you can either walk from there (15minutes), take a taxi (5minutes) or a direct bus. You can also park for free your car in our street (it is easy to find spaces). We have two bikes (one male and one female model) that you are more than welcome to use if you want to!
access: You'll be able to access all the flat and its equipment.
interaction: We will be happy to give you all the advices and information you would need (in French or in English) to allow you to enjoy the Scottish capital as much as we do! We love Edinburgh and Scotland and we hope you'll do as well. Don't hesitate to contact us if you need anything!
house_rules: Non smoker, pet-free, then nothing special except being as respectful as you can with the flat!
host_about:
I am a 29 years-old French woman expatriated in Edinburgh with my husband Laurent. We are both coming from Provence (Marseille) and after living for 6 years in Paris, we decided to move in Scotland 3 years ago and we are enjoying it! 
I am researcher in Biology at the University of Edinburgh and Laurent is working at the French Institute of Scotland. 
We love travelling, just the two of us or with family and friends, for long week-ends around Europe or longer travel around the world!
We are both thinking that it is great to stay in a true flat when we are travelling since it allows to live and enjoy the place as locals and to feel home.  After having great experiences as Airbnb guests, we decided to become hosts and to make you love Edinburgh and Marseille as much as we do!

name: Large and bright East London one bedroom flat
summary: Hello, my one bedroom flat is at the North East end of London Fields park, close to Hackney Central and London Fields station. The park has an open air pool in it - London Fields Lido - and is surrounded by lots of restaurants and bars - Broadway Market, E5 Bakery etc. Victoria Park is a ten minute walk, Hackney Central or London Fields stations 5 - 10 minutes walk. The flat is (in my opinion!) lovely and large for a one bedroom flat.
space: The flat is newly refurbished. It is bright, clean, large, with wooden floors throughout. There are large windows across the entire length of it so it feels very open and light. The open plan kitchen is all new with modern appliances including a coffee machine which you are more than welcome to make use of and a dishwasher so you can ignore the washing up! The separate bedroom has a double bed with plenty of linen and a mirrored wardrobe which you are free to use. The bathroom is tiled with an excellent hot shower, bath and towel heater. Towels provided. I also have a good stash of bubble bath which you can help yourself to! If you have extra guests, the sofa in the living room is as big as a single bed (I have slept on it when people have come to stay) and it is very comfy!
description: Hello, my one bedroom flat is at the North East end of London Fields park, close to Hackney Central and London Fields station. The park has an open air pool in it - London Fields Lido - and is surrounded by lots of restaurants and bars - Broadway Market, E5 Bakery etc. Victoria Park is a ten minute walk, Hackney Central or London Fields stations 5 - 10 minutes walk. The flat is (in my opinion!) lovely and large for a one bedroom flat. The flat is newly refurbished. It is bright, clean, large, with wooden floors throughout. There are large windows across the entire length of it so it feels very open and light. The open plan kitchen is all new with modern appliances including a coffee machine which you are more than welcome to make use of and a dishwasher so you can ignore the washing up! The separate bedroom has a double bed with plenty of linen and a mirrored wardrobe which you are free to use. The bathroom is tiled with an excellent hot shower, bath and towel heater. Towels provided.
neighborhood_overview: The best thing about the flat is its location. It is very near pretty much everything you might ever need. It is around the corner from London Fields park (2 minute walk), which has London Fields lido in it and is surrounded by nice places to eat and drink - there is a good bakery, a cinema, supermarkets, yoga places, a food market on Broadway Market on Saturdays, really good cafes and cakes on Wilton Way and 2 minutes walk from excellent restaurants. It is also two stops from Dalston on the overground; just South of Hackney Downs and Lower Clapton, ten minutes walk from Victoria Park; short bus ride to Bethnal Green. I can't list all the places here but very happy to share places I like with people if they want/need.
transit: 7 minutes walk to London Fields Overground which goes to Liverpool Street via Cambridge Heath. In the other direction: 7 minutes walk to Hackney Central, which gets you to Dalston and Islington in one direction and Hackney Wick and Stratford in the other. 10 minute direct bus to Bethnal Green tube which is on the Central line if you want to go into central London. And close to bus routes (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN) and lots of others.
access: The door to the flat is through a private entrance, with the flat itself on the second floor - so all very secure.  Access is with a fob. I do not have lift access I am afraid.
interaction: I am happy to provide you with information about the local area and also have substantial information on the flat which I will leave for guests. If I cannot meet you on arrival I will make sure you have all information you need for access in advance.
host_about: Hello, I joined Air BnB to travel more but I am now switching sides and operating as a host, since I have a nice one bed flat in a nice bit of  London. I have been living in the area for a couple of years and in London for six years. I work in the arts but I am increasingly interested in politics so currently studying a Masters degree in Political Science on top of my day job working for an artist.   Like many people in this neighbourhood I am quite into exercise. I like running, swimming and yoga - which are all well accommodated in the area. If any guests are into yoga then let me know as I can recommend good places. As is also common - I like my cooking, particularly indian food, and have a fairly comprehensive spice collection which guests are welcome to use! This is my first time renting out my flat so I don't yet have any reviews, other than an endorsement for me as a Guest when I stayed with a couple in Marseille. So as a reassurance I would like to add that the flat will be as you see it in the photos - I like to keep it clean, have managed to culture some pretty good plant life and I won't be around while you stay! Unless you need to be. As the flat  is my home and dear to my heart I would really like guests who are there to treat it like a home as well.

neighborhood_overview: In the heart of Hackney you are spoilt for things to do. Two large parks nearby (London Fields and Victoria Park) both with their own amenities. London Fields (5min walk) features an heated lido with swimming available all year round. Mare street has a plethora of bars, pubs and restaurants from Hackney Central all the way to Bethnal Green and boasts at least five craft breweries (Five Points, ELB, London Fields, MareGade and Howling Hops to name a few) which is a testament to some of the changes in culture we've seen in the last few years. Also situated right behind the Hackney Picture House cinema for a broader selection of films and the Hackney Empire for the various theatre, comedy and music events. Walk through London Fields on a Saturday and you'll be rewarded with a massive amount food and craft stalls, wonderful for lunch. On a Sunday if your legs don't mind walking a little further you can also smell the scents of Columbia Road flower market (09:00 - 15:00). Further afield the
notes: Towels and basic toiletries (toothpaste, shampoo, body wash) all supplied. As my daughter lives with me some of the time (not during guest visits) there are also lots of toys, kids books and cartoons for anyone staying with children.There's a spare laptop for you to use in the room and full access to the DVD library/NetFlix and Amazon Prime content.
transit: The flat is based at the heart of Hackney Central and is surrounded by plenty of transport links. 1.) Hackney Central Overground station (5 minute walk). 2.) London Fields / Hackney Downs Train station (10 minute walk). 3.) Buses into Central London ((PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN) within a 2 minute walk). 4.) Bus to Canary Wharf (277 within a 2 minute walk). 5.) Bicycle Rental 10 minute walk (bottom of London Fields in Broadway Market).
access: Full access to all the flat and its amenities. There's a shared walkway/balcony which fits a couple of chairs and table in the summer. On weekdays I receive guests between 06:00 and 08:00 or 18:00 and 00:00, weekends I am more flexible and will fit around your schedule.
interaction: I'm usually around during guest's stay and always happy to share a coffee or a beer. I love this area and I am always more than happy to help you find anywhere that may take your fancy. Tintin (the cat) does enjoy being looked after so don't be surprised if he finds a new home on your lap.
house_rules: Pretty relaxed flat, just respect that others live here too. you can smoke out on the balcony as this is a no smoking flat. Also make sure you keep the bathroom door closed when finished in the bathroom to make sure Tintin (the cat) doesn't get in!
host_about: Paris born and London bred I have lived in fair Hackney the last four years. I work in the Cloud industry which gives me the opportunity to be flexible with working hours and conditions, it gives me the chance to explore this amazing city and lends itself to my being able to live between London and Marseille. I'm currently studying PPH at night school so there's plenty of books on the shelves if you've forgotten to bring any. I have a passion for food and music and living in Hackney has plenty of opportunities to feed both those passions with ease, I'm always more than happy to share tips on places of interest and there's always fresh coffee waiting.

neighborhood_overview: I love living in this neighborhood and in this great city. I would be delighted to share my tips with you and to help you enjoy your stay, either I am in Paris or away. You will enjoy your stay in my perfectly located flat in the North Marais, the beating heart of Parisian contemporary creation. The 3rd arrondissement is one of the most exciting district. Home to many artists and designers, it is also an historic area, former residential place for XVIIth century aristocracy. Many ancient buildings are nowadays home to public museums (such as Musee Picasso, Musee de l'Histoire du Judaïsme, Musée de la Chasse et de la Nature).  In a village spirit, all amenities and places to see can be reached by foot.  If you like stroll around out of le Marais, many places of interest are within walking distance :  - place de la Bastille or de la République - less than 10 minutes  - Romantic river Seine or canal Saint Martin - less than 15 minutes  - Notre Dame, le Louvre and l’île Saint Louis - less
notes: I do love Paris, I have been living there for 20 years, and I ‘m in love with my neighborhood. I would be pleased to give you my secret tips. I prepare for you a notebook full of my favorite adresses…you can use it if I am not there to tell. The sofa is white and quite « fragile ». Please do not remove the pieces of fabric I put on the sitting place to protect it.

All information on public transportation website (website hidden)  Stations de Vélib et Autolib (bicycle and electric car self service)

Extremely accessible and close to downtown but at the same time like a little city on its own, the Beaches is where you need to be after spending the day  visiting around the city. The parks and the boardwalk by the lake will reinvigorate and relax you.
notes: Our neighbours are lovely and funny people, everybody will be extremely nice to you. However, try to avoid making loud noise after 10 PM and be considerate.
transit: The 501-Queen streetcar will leave you right in front of our building when stopping in "MacLean Ave". To go downtown, you just need to go on the other side of the street at "Glen Manor Ave" and get in the same streetcar going downtown. Another way would be to take the 64-Main bus at Wineva and Queen, which will bring you to Main Street subway station. From there, you will go Westbound to downtown. There are parking lots in front of our place (only certain hours) and in the adjacent streets. Parking fees may apply.
access: Guest will be able to enjoy and stay in the whole place.

Requests for early/late check in/out can always be made, but it's not guaranteed we can accept them. Check-IN times: Mon-Fri : 6PM to 11PM    Sat-Sun: 9AM to 3PM Check-OUT times: Mon-Fri: anytime before 4PM     Sat-Sun: anytime before 12 PM
host_about:
We are a young couple that enjoy meeting new people, having interesting conversations and building memories in our travels around the world. Affectionately known as "Pulcini" by family and friends, we are very down-to-earth and genuine people, inspired by simple values as love, hospitality and optimism.  Our place reflects our philosophy of life, being open, colorful and essential. The mix of Cuban and Italian backgrounds that characterize us always give our guests a boom of hospitality and friendliness. Our ideal night with people over will have soft music, good wine, flavorful dinner and witty conversations. 
We are madly in love with Paris, Madrid and Tulum; we listen to the Ibeyi, Jovanotti and The Beatles; we enjoy preparing (and mostly eating) Tiramisu, lasagna and butternut squash soup. 
Our motto? "Life is about moments : don't wait for them , create them "
Our dream is, one day, to open our own restaurant. It will be called "Cosa Nuestra", our thing. 
The next Pulcini's adventure will take place in Europe and Middle East: London, Brussels, northeast Italy, Israel, Malta, Marseille and Lisbon.
street: The Beaches, Toronto, ON M4E 1G7, Canada

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


Ich bin Architektin, lebe in Paris aber bin auch regelmässig in Südfrankreich (La Ciotat, Marseille) und Saarbrücken, wo ich geboren bin.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in the 10th arrondisement in the popular Canal Saint Martin neighborhood, one of the most sought after in Paris. The Canal is at the end of our street (15 second walk) and a perfect place for stroll, sitting in the sunshine or an outdoor picnic. The area is full of fantastic cafes, restaurants, bars, organic grocery stores, natural wine shops although our street is quiet (no bars on our street) with a Monoprix supermarket conveniently located across the street (open until midnight) a Vélib’ station on our doorstep and the famous bakery Pain et des Idées on the corner. We are a 10 minute walk to the fashionable Marais neighborhood with its many boutiques, gallery's, museums and restaurants. We are also 10 minutes walk from the lively Belleville neighborhood  with abundant Chinese, Vietnamese and North African restaurants. We are one street away from rue de Lancry full of hip bars and highly rated restaurants and a 20 minute walk to monmartre.
transit: The apartment is incredibly central and access to major metro stations are very close by. Metro Jacques Bonsergent is 1min walk away and connects directly to Gare du Nord and Gare de L'Est making it easy for airport access. We are 5 minutes walk from Republique which is a major metro hub, connecting many lines all over Paris. There is also a Vélib’ station on our doorstep for cycling around Paris if you wish.
access: Unlimited fast Wifi and cable television with Netflix. Sony TV screen with plug for hard drive and recording capabilities etc. Hifi system with iPod or iPhone connections and a Large library of art books and magazines.
interaction: You can contact us anytime with questions about the apartment or the area and we are more than happy to give you advise on anything. As we are both artists we have a large collection of art books please feel free to look at them but handle them carefully and put them back where you found them, thank you.

host_about:
FRANÇAIS (then ENGLISH)
Bonjour! 
Ravi de vous accueillir chez moi pendant votre séjour á Paris! 
J'ai pas mal voyagé sur tous les continents et vécu 3 ans au Perú: j'ai toujours aimé que l'on me fasse découvrir sa région, et j'adore aujourd'hui pouvoir faire découvrir la mienne (á Paris ou en Provence) aux ami-e-s du monde !! Je connais bien la ville et peut vous conseiller pas mal de chose, du tourisme classique au plus alternatif!
Vous verrez, le quartier de Ternes est très sympa, avec le fameux marché de la rue Poncelet (voir photos), une foule de restaurants de tous les horizons, et á deux pas de nombreux sites parisiens á connaitre (l'Arc de Triomphe, les Champs-Elysées, le Parc Monceaux, le Palais des Congrès, le Bois de Boulogne, etc...). De plus, on a rapidement accès á une foule de transports pour traverser la ville (ligne(URL HIDDEN)5mn, et á 10mn, RER A, lignes 1 et 6 ).
En ce qui me concerne, je suis un travailleur de la Solidarité Internationale (dans le « plaidoyer » c’est à dire les ONG qui conseillent/embêtent les gouvernements des pays développés pour une meilleure participation au développement des pays du Sud global) mais après 6 ans de bons et loyaux services en France et en Amérique Latine, je viens justement de reprendre un an d'étude á Paris. J'ai d'ailleurs aménagé mon chez moi pour m'y sentir bien durant les heures que j'y passe á réviser ou me détendre.. Vous apprécierez ce petit nid. 
Je suis très amateur de musique et de cinéma, j'ai donc un excellent système audio (ADAM A5X) pour écouter la musique, et un vidéoprojecteur, que vous etes évidemment bienvenu-e-s á utiliser pour aller au cinéma… tranquille chez soi ! 
Enfin, j'aime bien manger! Et la proximité du (très joli) marché Poncelet, oú l'on trouve vraiment les meilleurs produits du pays, est précieux pour les bons diners. La cuisine, très bien équipée, est á votre entière disposition. 
Si vous préférer manger dehors, vous trouverez dans le quartier une foule de très bons petits restaurants, du bons petit plats au menu gastronimque, je peux vous conseiller. Et n'oubliez pas de passer á la Boulangerie Niel, á 100m, qui est véritablement la meilleure du quartier ("de la ville" j'ai envie de dire.. mais j'ai des amis qui me le disputent...)
J'espère en tout cas que vous aimerez Paris et ses parisiens qui (étonnement ;) ont une sulfureuse réputation !!
Bon voyage et bienvenu-e-s ! 
reno

ENGLISH
Hello Hi,
Really happy to welcome you in my flat during your travel to Paris! :)

I have traveled pretty much on all continents including I lived 3 years in Perú: i have always liked having people making me discover their regions and i now like having people from the world discovering mine (in Paris ou in the south around Marseille)!
I know well Paris and can advise you on many things, from classical tourism to more alternative options.
You will see, Ternes area is really nice, with its famous farmers market in Poncelet street (see pictures) and a bunch of very diverse restaurants all around. You will find various touristical sites very close (Arc of Triomph, Champs Elysées, the amazing Monceaux Parc, the Palais des Congrès, Boulogne Hood, etc...). In addition, you have all key metro lines very close (ligne 2 and 3 within 5mn, and RER (express) A and ligne 1 and 6 à 10mn).

About me, I am working in international development (advocacy NGOs) but after years of work from Paris and from Latinamerica, I recently got back to paris in order to study during a year. That's why i have set up such a cosy space of life in my flat: to handle long hours of home work, and it works: I and people feel good at my place. :)
I love music and cinema, so i have a very good music system (ADAMX5) and a video projector that you are welcome to use: it 's really cool to be like at cinema... at home!
Lastly, I like good food. And the (very cute) market of Poncelet where you will find excellent farm and traditional product is really precious for good dinner. The kitchen is well equiped (oven, microwave, coffee maker, teepot, freezer etc....)
If you prefer to eat outside, you will find a lot of very good restaurants, from cute small places to serious gastronomic menus;i can advise you. And don't forget to give a try to the 100m away Boulangerie Niel (bakers and cake shop) that really is the best in the area ('of the city' i would actually say, but some friends would dispute that..) 

I really hope you will like Paris and its people who (surprisingly) have such a bad reputations!! ;)

Safe travel and welcome! 
Bon voyage et bienvenu-e-s !
reno

name: 2 pièces cocooning et chaleureux
summary: Charmant appartement 2 pièces meublé avec soin, confortable et élégant (40 m2, 1er niv) proche de la place de la Nation (transports) et du cimetière du Père Lachaise. Parfait pour découvrir le Paris authentique et les quartiers animés de la capitale.
space: Cet appartement est à la fois dans Paris et en même temps dans un quartier très calme et plein de charme.  Ce dernier est composé d'une chambre, d'un salon, d'une cuisine tout équipée qui vous permettra de préparer de bons petits plats, une machine Nespresso pour les amoureux du café. Il y a du parquet au sol ce qui le rend chaleureux. Il est également très lumineux tout au long de la journée. La literie est de très bonne qualité et la chambre comporte de nombreux rangements. Vous n'avez plus qu'à arriver avec vos bagages et à vous installer "comme à la maison". Attention la télévision ne fonctionne pas! merci par avance de votre compréhension.

neighborhood_overview: Quartier animé, convivial et encore populaire; Il se compose de nombreuses petites rues au charme atypique. Il y a deux marchés différents qui permettent de faire les courses et de nombreuses boutiques(boulangerie, boucherie, traiteur..) très pratiques au quotidien. La rue sur laquelle donne l'appartement est calme et peu passante. Il n'y a aucun vis à vis et la proximité de nombreux squares et du Père Lachaise permet de faire de jolies balades toutes proches de l'appartement. Le quartier permet de découvrir le "vrai" Paris authentique.
transit: C'est un lieu bien desservi par tous les transports en commun(bus, métro, RER) et cela permet donc de se déplacer très facilement dans la ville et d'accéder à l'hyper centre en 15 minutes.
access: Les voyageurs auront accès à tout l'appartement et seront seuls durant leur séjour.
interaction: Je ne serai pas présente durant le séjour mais simplement là pour l'accueil et la visite mais disponible à tout moment par téléphone pour répondre à leurs éventuelles questions.
house_rules: I please ask that you take off your shoes as much as possible when entering the apartment. The tenants below will greatly appreciate that plus the dirt and grime from the busy Paris streets can stay outside ;) appartement non fumeur/ You can't smoke inside
host_about: une fille simple et naturelle qui a les pieds sur terre.  La plupart du temps j'ai du mal à m'arrêter lorsque je commence quelque chose.  Je suis franche et honnête, Ennemie de la superficialité. Parfois je recherche la sécurité et à me rassurer dans une vie sédentaire et routinière, alors que parfois je cherche le changement et l'aventure. J'aime par dessus tout le cinéma, les animaux et la nature. Carpe Diem!

host_about:
Hi, I'm Pauline, I'm 22. 
I am a french young designer/scenographer. After two years spent in Montréal, Canada, and a trip in USA, I'm back in France for few months. I love discover new places, new cultures, and hang out with cool people. 
I do a lot of goings and comings between Marseille and Paris (essentially because of job) so maybe I'll not be there during your journey, but my adorable boyfriend Thomas will be present to welcome you :)

Thomas is a law and international relations student. He's very very sociable, cheerful and welcoming ! We share our lovely 2 bedrooms apartment in the heart of Paris, next to Montmartre.

It will be our pleasure to host you or to travel in your place :)

Mon dernier voyage: Georgie et Turquie pendant deux mois avec mon copain où nous avons d'ailleurs fais une semaine de rbnb à Istanbul!

host_about:
Hi!

young professional in her thirties, lived in Rome, Paris Singapore, Beijing and  Brussels before relocating to Paris. Strong appetite for writing, traveling and meeting with people. 2014 trips include Siciliy, Hamburg, Oman, Ireland, Copenhagen, Porto, Camino de Santiago in Spain, Marseille, Dubai, Berlin, Stockholm, Croatia, Bosnia, Barcelona, London, Warsaw, NYC, Morocco, Oslo and Bergen, Cambridge-UK,  Romania and Tuscany for New Year's Eve, and San Francisco in February. Next on my mind: the Transsiberian  
For French speakers, I also run a blog on food and restaurant ((website hidden)), so I look forward to sharing your favorite addresses!
I travel as soon as I get 2 or 3 days off, to discover cities I've never been, to meet some friends or revisit some places I like. My passport is always in my bag, my bag packed light. 
My bedtime readings: "1000 places to see before you die" and the New York Times "36 Hours 125 Weekends in Europe" . 

Hope to meet you soon!
Juliette

Hi I'm Mathieu, 28 years old. I was born in Marseille and I live for 7 years in Paris. I came here to study photography in Art School. I love this city, every district got its charm and is full of treasures. You will be always surprise to discover new places, bars, restaurants, galeries or librairies… I only miss one thing: the sea. But any city is perfect ;)

One advice: forget the subway and take the Velib', it's the best way to appreciate the beauty of Paris.

I hope you will great time here,

 Mathieu
